title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix flakes with butter; press 1 cup of mix in bottom of pie pan.

title: chicken cacciatore(to catch a man!)
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In large frypan brown chicken in oil. Add remaining ingredients, except pepper and mushrooms.
Stir well. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms. Cook 15 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with noodles or spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: go to church casserole
directions: Arrange hamburger, onion and potatoes in layers, seasoning to taste.
Add soup and milk.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour, or bake for 2 hours at 250°, until potatoes are tender.
Cover with cheese the last 15 minutes, if desired.

title: spicy shrimp creole
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet.
Mix in celery, both onions, green pepper, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat stirring frequently for 10 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes longer.
Mix in salt, chili powder and celery seed.
Cook over very low heat for 1 hour.
Add the shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan; bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: shannon casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain fat.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, cottage cheese and tomato sauce.
Add beef and cooked noodles to sauce and mix well.
Bake at approximately 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until top is bubbling.)
Serve with a little Parmesan cheese sprinkled.
It's delicious!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken breasts.
Mix first 7 ingredients with 3 cups of broth.
Put in greased casserole dish. Mix 2 cups Rice Krispies with 1/2 stick melted margarine and put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.
Add grated cheese if desired. If you freeze, do not put Rice Krispies on until ready to cook.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Clean
and
wash
beans.
Add
to
the gallon of water. Cover and
bring
to a boil.
Cook for 1 hour over a low fire. After the beans have cooked for 1 hour, add the ham, or bacon, onions, celery,
green peppers, tomatoes and continue to cook for an additional 45 minutes under a low fire.
With 2 tablespoons of flour,
mix a smooth mixture of flour and water and add
to
the soup,
stirring
to make a smooth textured soup. Serve as an appetizer, or as a main course meal.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: walnut pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Blend marinade with garlic and basil.
Chop artichokes. Toss with pasta, mushrooms, tomatoes, onion and marinade mixture. Cover and chill.
Toss in walnuts before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade chili for hot dogs
directions: Brown ground round.
Saute celery and onion.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon over grilled hot dogs.
Good for a cook out.
Serves 10.

title: breakfast punch
directions: Blend together in blender lemon juice and bananas.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Boil together until dissolved water and sugar.
Combine all ingredients, then freeze.
Thaw two hours ahead of serving time.
When serving, add one 2-liter bottle of diet 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in greased casserole dish. Save a little cheese and a few green onions to put on top. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: company chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken half in a strip of bacon.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef. Cover with chicken.
Cover with a mixture of soup and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Bake covered for 2 hours, then uncover for final 1 1/2 hours.

title: bavarian pot roast(or goulash)
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces or leave whole.
Brown in hot fat/oil.
When the meat is browned on all sides, add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over medium noodles.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: won ton skin snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut package of won ton skins diagonally. Separate won tons and dip in water.
Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Sprinkle each triangle with Parmesan cheese, cinnamon sugar or No Salt seasoning blend.
Bake until crisp and toasted.
Store in tightly closed container or plastic bags.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix ingredients. Add pineapple juice, if too dry. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Put shrimp into blender. Add cream cheese, margarine, salad dressing, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Turn on to blend. Remove from blender and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: chocolate covered pecans
directions: Unwrap caramels and warm very little.
Wrap caramels around 1 or 2 pecan halves.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double broiler.
Dip wrapped pecans in mixture and place on wax paper. Let harden.

title: milk shake
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Add 6 to 8 ice cubes.
Process until ice cubes are mushy.
Can add fresh fruit for variety (bananas or strawberries are great).

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in egg, onion and buttermilk.
Do not mix too long.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter together.
Pack 2/3 of the mixture on bottom and sides of 9x13x2 inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: german potato soup
directions: Peel, quarter and slice potatoes. Combine with water and all seasonings. Cook for 30 to 40 minutes. Dice bacon; fry. Add diced onion and fry until brown. Put in with potatoes. Add wieners or smoked sausage until heated. Eat with soup.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add corn, noodles, celery, parsley, salt and pepper.
Boil 5 minutes; then add chicken.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs, if desired.

title: confetti dip
directions: Mix all in bowl.
Cover; marinate 24 hours or overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp sauce and pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little oil; add seasoned salt and shrimp, saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Add wine and whipping cream.
Cook until skim forms on top.
Pour over cooked pasta.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook macaroni to box directions; melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, cooking until it bubbles.
Slowly stir in milk, adding salt.
Cook until thick, then add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Combine with macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.

title: honey cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add oil, honey and sour cream.
Beat well.
Sift and add:
flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour 2 small loaf pans or 8 small margarine tins.
Fill 2/3 full. Place on cookie sheet if using small tins.
Bake on middle rack at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter and press onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: tortilla roll-ups(mexican)
directions: Blend all ingredients except tortillas.
(Blending in a food processor is quicker and easier.)
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice into bite size pieces before serving.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate and serve with gingersnaps or sliced apples.

title: poor man's salisbury steak
directions: Chop onions and mix with ground beef and your favorite seasonings.
Pat ground beef into 8 hamburgers and fry until they are done completely.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with tinfoil and put 1 can each of cream of mushroom and cream of celery soup.
Put half a can of mushrooms in the bottom, also.
Put in the hamburgers.
Cover the hamburgers with the remaining cans of soup and mushrooms.
Cover with more tinfoil.
Bake in the oven at 350° until gravy is thoroughly cooked.
Enjoy!

title: sugar cookie cutouts
directions: Cream the butter, eggs, sugar and sour cream together well. Add remaining ingredients and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread on bottom of dish.

title: beef stew(slow cooker)
directions: Put in cooker in order.
Stir.
Cover; set on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: canned squash or okra
directions: Place squash or okra in a large pot.
Barely cover with water. Add canning salt and vinegar.
Bring to a light boil. Boil gently until squash or okra changes color.
Pack into jars.
Pour liquid into jars over squash or okra.
Seal.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with spices, 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Mix like a fruit cake.
Line pan with foil.
Bake in oven 1 hour or until done.
Not too sweet.
Excellent choice for Christmas holidays.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Put all of these ingredients into a blender and mix until well blended.

title: quick hot potato salad
directions: Combine bacon and potatoes.
Coat with dressing.
Allow to simmer for a few minutes to combine flavors.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture to form dough.
Roll into ball and set aside.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Beat together sugar, butter, peanut butter and egg with mixer until creamy.
Add milk and flour until blended.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle peanuts and chocolate chips over top.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: crescent meltaways(cookies)
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup butter and flour.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 4 balls.
Roll one ball at a time onto floured surface.
Roll into a circle.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar/cinnamon mixture and nuts.
Cut into 16 pie shaped pieces and roll from wide end placing point down onto greased cookie sheet.

title: chili sauce #1
directions: Brown meat with onion.	Add the rest of ingredients and mix. Simmer for 1 hour.	Fill clean jars.
Seal and hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: margarita-aggie
directions: Mix well and pour over cracked ice or blend with ice in a blender for a frozen Margarita.
Garnish with a lime wedge.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Rinse and drain black beans.
Drain corn.
Combine all ingredients and toss well.
Serve with tortilla chips, with tacos, or on grilled fish.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Fix rice as usual.
Mix in picante sauce.
Cover with cheese.

title: batter for pancakes or waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour onto greased, hot frypan or griddle or use waffle iron according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 15 pancakes.

title: green beans with cheese
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over hot beans.
If desired, drain one 4-ounce can sliced mushrooms and brown in butter.
Use for trim.
Serves 4.

title: berried delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter together. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan; chill.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk; then add 1 3/4 cups Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust.
At this point, you can put bananas between this layer and pudding layer.
Mix jello and milk; pour over cream cheese layer.
Top with 1 3/4 cups Cool Whip.
Top with sliced strawberries.

title: cinnie's seafood salad
directions: Shred crab in food processor or cut finely.
Add thawed, rinsed and well drained shrimp.
Add ground or mashed eggs and rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: gil's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Store in empty ketchup bottle.
Good on ribs.

title: russian tea(beverage)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir
2 teaspoons into a cup of hot water.
Stir and Serve.

title: baked challah bread casserole
directions: Spray foil lasagna pan with Pam.
Lay bread on the bottom. Spread cheese and mushrooms on bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour in pan.
Let pan sit for a few hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon over your favorite salad.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak generously.
Beat in as much flour as steak will take.
Brown in 3 tablespoons fat. Pour sliced sweet onion and bell pepper over steak.
Mix together catsup, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over onions.
Cover.
Bake for 45 minutes in moderate oven (300° to 350°).
Then add tomatoes.
Cook until steak is very tender.
Total cooking time is approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue spareribs(yields 5 servings)
directions: Parboil spareribs in salted water for 45 minutes.
Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Dip cooked ribs in sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over all ribs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage and potato chowder
directions: In a large, deep saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove. Set aside.
Leave 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion and red pepper; saute for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Blend in soup, broth and cream.
Add cabbage, cauliflower, broccoli, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, just until vegetables are tender. Gradually blend in cheese.
Garnish with bacon.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Empty dry cake mix into mixing bowl.
Add eggs and pie filling; mix well.
Pour half into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half of the cinnamon sugar.
Pour in rest of mix; top with rest of cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: nachos spread
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add whipping cream, Velveeta cheese, chili beans, chili and tomatoes.
Cook until smooth. Serve over hot tostados.
Top with lettuce and whatever else.

title: quick bread puffs
directions: Heat cooking oil 1 inch deep in frypan.
Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in very hot oil. Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: wonderful cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to recipe on box.
Make holes in warm cake and pour sweetened condensed milk onto cake in pan.
Then pour pina colada mix on top of that.
Let cool, then put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Leave cake in pan to cool.

title: cranberry poached pears
directions: Combine cranapple juice, spices and brown sugar in saucepan. Add pears and bring to a boil.
Simmer gently 1 hour. Cool and refrigerate pears in juice overnight.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown beef and onion in a frypan.
Stir in chili mix.
Add tomato paste and canned tomatoes; simmer until mixture thickens. Add pinto beans and boil for 10 minutes.
If desired, extra chili powder may be added for extra hot chili.

title: harland's clamatto soup
directions: In medium size pot, empty cans of soup.
Add milk, salt, pepper, butter and just the juice of the clams.
Put clams aside. Heat on medium, stirring constantly until it bubbles; reduce heat. Dice clams and add, then cook until soup is hot.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done; cool and cube in a bowl.
Add eggs, celery, onion, bell pepper, sweet relish, salt and pepper.
Mix; add mayonnaise and mustard.
Potatoes may vary so more Miracle Whip may be added.
Garnish with paprika.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour 1/2 contents into Pyrex baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Let remainder set at room temperature.
Place in refrigerator until molded.
Top with 16 ounces sour cream and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Add remaining mixture and place in refrigerator until molded.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice). Mix pineapple with marshmallows and sit aside in fridge.

title: burgundy pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and pour into a 10-inch lined pastry dish.
Dot with butter and place top crust on.
Bake at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with onion; drain.
Mix soup, sauces and chiles with meat mixture.
Layer three times:
chips, meat and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: creamy cornmeal
directions: Mix. Bake at 425° until done in an iron skillet.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffins) together.
Spread on English muffins and freeze.
Whenever you need them for a party or get-together, remove from freezer and place into a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then put under broiler until brown.

title: erin go bragh irish brown soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and sprinkle a baking sheet lightly with flour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan; sprinkle graham cracker crumbs.
Sieve Ricotta cheese into large bowl.
Add cream cheese. Beat on high speed.
Beat in sugar, then eggs.
Reduce speed. Beat in cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla, then margarine and sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes until firm.
Turn oven off; let cake stand in oven for 2 hours. Remove and chill.
Remove sides of pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl with nuts.
Mix well. Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
When cool, add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture a bit at a time.
Add half chocolate chips to mixture and place in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion then drain.
Stir in water, bay leaf, salt, pepper, undrained tomatoes and the season mix from Hamburger Helper box.
Break tomatoes up with a fork.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add in noodles and vegetables; cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: spicy hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients until dry ingredients are moistened. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep, hot oil, fry only a few at a time, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes or until hush puppies are golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: company best pickles
directions: Place whole cucumbers
in
a
glass
or
stoneware jar; cover with
boiling
water.
Let
stand
overnight;
drain. Repeat 3 times.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces. Combine sugar, spices,
salt and vinegar;
bring to a boil.
Pour over
pickles; let stand for 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil and pack in hot jars and seal.

title: quick and easy ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Put ham in shell first.
Then add broccoli and cheese.
Mix heavy cream and Egg Beaters.
Pour into pie shell.
Place sliced tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: hearty beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix together beef, broccoli and 1 can onions.
Spread over potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cheese and seasonings in small saucepan; heat.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with 1 can onions and remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and onions are brown, approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scott's cheese spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients listed except the party rounds. Cover the top of each round with the spread and broil in oven until the spread is hot and starts to bubble. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 cups.
Makes a nice gift and freezes very well.

title: pat's salsa
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; let cook for about 5 minutes.
Add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls salt.
Put into jars and seal.
You can make salsa to whatever consistency you like by the way you prepare your tomatoes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together with fork to make dough.
Roll out thin and cut into strips.
Drop in boiling broth. Cook until done.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together
and put in a large baking dish. Put strip of pork or bacon on the top. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with Fritos and Dorito chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse in cold water.
In large bowl mix spaghetti, bell pepper, red onion, cucumber and tomato.
In large cup, combine vinegar, oil and salad seasoning.
Stir well and pour over spaghetti mixture.
Refrigerate, stirring every few hours.
Best if made a day early so all ingredients marinate.

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, mixing well to melt peanut butter.
Add corn flakes; stir to mix well.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.
(I just spread into a greased pan and cut into pieces when cool.)

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: First, mix together first 3 ingredients; if dry, add a little milk.
Chill for 1 hour; form into balls.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Dredge thickly with flour.
Fry in hot oil, browning well on both sides.
Drain; place on serving dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add butter to pan fryings; blend in flour and add milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over tomatoes and serve.

title: pineapple "delight" cake
directions: Bake the cake according to directions using a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool.
Combine sugar and pineapple, heating and stirring, until sugar dissolves.

title: southern yam cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; heat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Stir up potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best for layer cake.

title: cottage cheese-potato scallop
directions: Cook potatoes with jacket on.
Peel and slice and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion, salt and pepper over potatoes. Combine cottage cheese and sour cream and spoon over potatoes. Top with Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff (skillet)
directions: Saute beef in 1/2 of oleo in heavy skillet.
In another skillet, saute with remaining oleo, mushrooms, onions and garlic until clear.
Combine with beef.
Add catsup, vinegar and sour cream.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hot rice or noodles.

title: "german" dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil, then cool.
(Best done the night before.)
Fill quart jars with fresh crisp cucumbers (whole).
Add alum, dill and garlic to jars.
Add pickling syrup and seal.
Wait 2 weeks, preferably 6, before you sample, to give the pickles a chance to reach their flavor peak.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and Cool Whip together.
Add pineapple; mix well.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in greased 11 x 7-inch casserole dish. Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Slice chicken and arrange on top of broccoli.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese and then buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 or more.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain and flake fish.
Add all ingredients except flour and oil.
(More wheat germ may be added if mixture is too wet.)
Form into six 2-inch patties.
Roll in flour and fry in a small amount oil (approximately 1/2 inch in skillet).
Drain.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until tender.
Let cool, then peel off skins and shred potatoes in shredder.
Mix with soft butter, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir all together with onion.
Put mixture in a long, glass pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind up vegetables.
Put in pan and add the rest of ingredients.
Cook about 1 3/4 hours or until it thickens.

title: chili
directions: Sear meat.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and beer.
Stir in all ingredients except flour.
Cover pot and simmer 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Stir flour into warm water to make a thick flowable paste.
Add to chili.
Simmer additional 15 to 20 minutes.
If desired, add beans now.

title: turkey scaloppini
directions: Pound and flour meat.
Saute in olive oil until golden brown. Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In pan over high heat, add wine, garlic and oregano.
Sprinkle flour and blend. Add mushrooms and stir until mushrooms are covered.
Add chicken and turn until covered with sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: eastbrook cherry crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch glass dish.
Place pie filling on the bottom.
Crumble cake mix on top.
Sprinkle pecans over cake. Drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: mignonne's spinach bread
directions: Drain spinach and squeeze dry with paper towel; set aside. Cut rolls in half lengthwise; spread with 1/4 cup softened margarine.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Add cheese roll, stirring until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; add spinach, Worcestershire sauce and pepper, stirring well.
Spread spinach mixture on bread, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve immediately. Yields 12 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch square cake pan.
Melt butter or shortening over low heat or in microwave.
Add brown sugar.
Cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: Stir grits into boiling water.
Add salt.
Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, cheese and hot sauce, stirring until butter and cheese melts

title: apple pie
directions: Get a glass pie pan.
Put your pie at the bottom and then put the peeled apples, the spice and milk in this order.
Then make dough.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 9-inch cake pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool and spread on Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Soften yeast in small amount of buttermilk heated to lukewarm. Add remaining buttermilk and salad oil.
Beat in the 3 cups of flour; add sugar mixed with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add remaining cup of flour and knead on lightly floured surface. Grease top of dough and place in refrigerator until ready for use. About 2 hours before baking, form into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: lemon-shrimp pasta
directions: In pan over medium heat, combine vinegar, lemon juice, honey, ginger, garlic and soy sauce.
Add shrimp and bring to a boil. Stir for 3 to 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Lift out shrimp with slotted spoon, reserving liquid.
Cover and refrigerate shrimp.
In separate pan, cook fettucine for 15 minutes and drain.
In large bowl, combine pasta, reserved liquid, shrimp, sesame oil, onions and lemon peel.
Mix lightly.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole with butter or cooking spray.
Cook broccoli, cutting extra large pieces.
Mix broccoli, soup, cheese, beaten egg, milk, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Spread mixture into greased casserole.
Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs and sprinkle evenly over top of mixture. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first three ingredients until creamed (best if mixer is used).
Add sifted flour and sifted baking powder with salt to creamed mixture.
(I refrigerate a few hours or few days.)
Take out and roll on floured pastry cloth.
Cut into desired shapes and bake on 350° until very lightly browned on bottom, 5-7 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: juicy salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° in oven for 35 minutes, or until firm and light brown on top.

title: pan fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk, then shake in bag containing salt and pepper.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix
first 6 ingredients.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2 dish.
Cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine the thawed and drained vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Uncover and bake for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: Cut turkey necks up and flour lightly.
Saute in butter until brown.
Combine turkey and broth and simmer covered for 40 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Simmer for 20 minutes more.
Add more broth if desired and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: shortcut lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add tomato juice, tomato sauce and dry spaghetti mix.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix the 3 cheeses together.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage, drain and spread on paper towel to cool well. Break into small pieces.
Roll 1 loaf of bread at a time on unfloured surface, then roll up tight like a jelly roll.
Pinch seam together, brush with melted butter and put, seam side down, on a cookie sheet.
Cut slits on top of loaf.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do second loaf, let cool and slice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place a grape leaf in bottom of each quart jar.
Fill with cucumbers.
Add the spices in each jar.
Boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and spices.
Seal.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over hot water.
In separate bowl combine eggs, sugar, milk; add vanilla and blend thoroughly. Add chocolate and margarine mixture.
Turn into greased pan and chill.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant in thick slices.
Brown in drippings or butter.
Lay on plate.
Mix onions, green pepper, and tomatoes in frying pan.
Add small amount of flour.
Season with salt, pepper, and oregano.
Fill casserole with alternating layers of eggplant and tomato mixture.
Bake in uncovered dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water.
In a greased casserole alternate a layer of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cover and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: stuffed peppers(the easy way)
directions: Cut up peppers.
Cook hamburg; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, garlic, basil, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for at least 10 minutes.
In bowl, combine egg, remaining salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce; beat with spoon to blend.
Mix hamburg, egg mixture, rice and tomato mixture.
Add cut up peppers.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Place crackers in a single layer on the foil.
Melt butter and sugar together and pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Using a spoon spread the chocolate as it melts.
Sprinkle with pecans and freeze for 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in a tin in the freezer.

title: mom's hot applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add hot applesauce.
Add next 8 ingredients. Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Add to cake mixture, stir quickly.
Pour into 1 greased tube or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: snap bean casserole
directions: Saute onions.
Add snap beans and cook for 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt cheese with cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel.
Pour over snap beans.
Add Italian bread crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Place potatoes, broth and water (if needed) to cover potatoes in pot.
Bring to boiling.
Lower the heat and simmer 5 minutes. Drain.
Save broth for soup.
Transfer potatoes to bowl.
Heat olive oil in saucepan over low heat.
Whisk in flour.
Heat 1 minute.
Add milk, stirring to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes.
Stir gently. Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are tender.
After 30 minutes baking, sprinkle on crumb topping:

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients.
Pour into three pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: zareens' shrimp curry
directions: Shell the shrimp.
Devein the shrimp by making a shallow incision in back to lift out dark substance.
Wash and combine with salt.
Leave for 15 minutes.
Blend coconut, coriander seed and water at high speed until pureed.
Extract water on paper towel.
Discard pulp and put coconut mixture aside.
Heat the vegetable oil.
Drop in vegetable oil and cook for 30 seconds until shrimp are pink.
Add ginger, oil and garlic; fry 1 minute. Add onions; fry for 7 to 8 minutes, until brown.
Add spices; stir for 1 minute.
Add shrimp marinade.
Return shrimp to skillet. Return coconut mixture.
Reduce heat and top with 2 tablespoons of coriander and cover.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil then pour over the gallon of cucumber and onions.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: jalapeno chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir frequently.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ham and split pea soup
directions: Wash and sort peas.
Place in a large pot and add water; bring to a boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add ham bone, vegetables, bay leaf and thyme. Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until peas are soft.
Remove bone; cut off meat and dice. Return meat to soup.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: steamed holiday pudding
directions: *If using self-rising flour, decrease soda to 1/2 teaspoon.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and water, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter. Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Dip a fork in water to flatten cookies to 1/4-inch in a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields about 8 dozen.

title: vegetable quiche cups to go
directions: Microwave the spinach for 2 1/2 minutes on High. Drain the excess liquid. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with foil baking cups. Spray the cups with cooking spray. Combine the egg substitute, cheese, peppers, onions and spinach in a bowl. Mix well. Divide evenly among the muffin cups. Bake at 360°
for 20 minutes, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs well together.
Put them in a wheat field.
Stir gently.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Sprinkle field with flowers; spread over all a deep blue sky, and bake in sun.
Yield:
1 quart laughter.
When brown, set away to cool in bathtub.
Let rest.

title: hot nacho sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and pepper in grease.
Add tomatoes, flour, chili powder and green chiles.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir on low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.
Makes about 5 cups. Freezes well!

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve gelatin, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Put in Dixie cups.
Freeze.
Place popsicle sticks in after about 1 hour.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix together in a bowl and shake.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble and brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off excess fat.
In a slow cooking pot, combine all ingredients and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: reese peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with Reese's pieces.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter in bottom of pan.
Five or 6 slices apples on top of butter.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat in foil
directions: You will also need 6 (18 x 12-inch) pieces of heavy-duty foil.

title: orange fruit cake(very good)
directions: Use 1/4 cup flour to roll dates (chopped) and nuts in.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add orange rind.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix juice of 2 oranges and 2 tablespoons grated rind with 2/3 cup sugar.
Dissolve.
Pour over warm cake.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken splendid
directions: Grease pan with Pam.
Line large oblong casserole with dried beef.
Roll each chicken breast and wrap with slice of bacon. Place chicken on top of beef.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large saucepan, brown hamburger, green pepper and onion in margarine; drain well.
Add water, Worcestershire and catsup to the hamburger mixture and simmer.
Serve on warm hamburger buns.
Serves 8.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir well.
Add Coke and let set up a little.
Add cherry pie mix.
Stir
and
let set.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and chicken pieces in broth.
Mix all ingredients and bake for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: mom's steak marinade(hand me down recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in shallow dish.
Pierce steak with meat fork and coat both sides with the marinade.
Allow meat to marinate in the refrigerator for several hours to absorb the most flavor.
Grill or broil steak to desired doneness.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread coconut and pecans in pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter over coconut and pecans.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of batter.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, raisins and sour cream in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil five to six minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add beaten eggs, stir vigorously. Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust and serve.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Mix together and let stand refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage (235°).
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Drop onto foil.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Dice veggies and bacon in small sizes.
Mix in a large pan with beans.
Cover for 2 hours at 325°; then uncover for last hour.

title: chocolate chess pie(makes 3 pies)
directions: Beat liquid ingredients (eggs and milk) and slowly add dry (sugar, flour and cocoa, mixed together) to mixture.
Mix well and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Baked pies will puff up in approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
The tops will be crusty.
Eat one, freeze one and give the other away.
Such is the joy of cooking.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix sour cream, green pepper, garlic salt, onion and beef.
Place in baking dish.
Saute pecans in dab of butter.
Sprinkle over dip. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup and sugar with melted oleo.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans to syrup and mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 15 minutes and then lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Do not overcook.

title: grilled pizza(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Lightly brush 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with olive oil.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion in baking dish.
Top with potato chips and sprinkle melted butter on top. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: ground beef and tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick product.
Spread ground beef on bottom.
Layer 2 chopped bell peppers and 2 chopped onions on top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese.
Layer 1 bag of tater tots. Sprinkle with 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix all three soups together and spread on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter and maple rice krispers
directions: Mix syrup and sugar. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon out on waxed paper. Can be rolled into miniature logs and even dipped in melted chocolate and paraffin.

title: peppernuts(german cookie)
directions: Mix baking soda in a little warm water.
Mix baking powder in with flour and combine with baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients with enough flour to make a stiff dough.
When adding eggs, do so one at a time.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out into rolls as big as your finger. Cut rolls in small pieces. Roll in the palms of your hands to make small balls, about 1 inch in size.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yield: 1000 cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar together and let stand for 15 to 30 minutes.
Add the marshmallows, grapes, Cool Whip, salt, apples and walnuts.
Chill until serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 medium-size loaves.

title: calico beans
directions: Put all into a crock-pot.
Cook until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Sprinkle miniature chocolate chips into pie shell.
Prepare pie filling mix as directed on package for pie, using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped topping and pour over chocolate chips in pie shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with curls of chocolate.

title: cherished coconut wine cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat sugar with the eggs until combined.
Add the oil, white wine, vanilla and flour mixture.	Beat on low for 1 minute.
Divide the batter between the 2 well-buttered, floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Let layers cool in pans on racks for 10 minutes, then invert onto racks to cool completely.

title: meat loaf
directions: Toss all ingredients together, mixing lightly, but thoroughly. Spoon mixture evenly into 1-quart utility dish.
Do not pack. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes on level #7.
Use sol-cook setting on rr-7d.
Make a sauce with ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire; pour over loaf and bake for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Coat with flour and brown in skillet.
Add broth and mustard.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Grind garlic, green pepper and onion; add hot pepper and Tabasco.
Add to shrimp.
Cream the cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise together; add salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Much better if made a day ahead.
Use with toasted tortilla chips, potato chips, etc.
Serves approximately 20.

title: hot mulled cidar
directions: This wuz a grate spring tonic thet wuz both a treatmint 'n a treat!

title: macaroni-potato salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Separate egg yolks; mash and chill.
Chop egg whites.
Put in large bowl with macaroni and potatoes.
Stir in salt and vinegar. Chill overnight.
Add egg yolks and remaining ingredients.
Gently mix into macaroni mixture.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk on low speed on mixer to remove large lumps.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels. Pour batter into a greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Steep tea bags in a pint of water for 5 minutes.
Add to boiling mixture. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to boil and serve hot.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Lay bacon on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and place into a casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add no salt.
It is plenty salty.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease pan well.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 375° until golden brown.

title: crunchy cheese baked tomatoes
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes in half.
Place cut side up in baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine cheese, bread crumbs, pecans, butter, basil and creole seasoning.
Blend well.
Spoon approximately 1 heaping tablespoonful cheese mixture on top of each tomato.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes. Be sure the baking pan used is filled 1/4 with warm water before baking.
If large tomatoes, cut in half and serve 8 or use medium-size and serve 4.

title: pickled vidalia onion relish
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Add shortening; mix until crumbly.
Add beaten egg and enough cold water to make a stiff dough.
Add vinegar; mix well and form into 3 balls.
You may use right away or chill for later use.
May also be frozen for later use.
Makes 3 pies.

title: weekday cheese and pasta supper(1 serving)
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil; salt it generously and throw in the pasta. Let it boil, loosening any stuck pasta from the bottom of the pot with a long spoon until tender, about 9 minutes, depending on the shape of the pasta. (Tubes such as rigatoni take longer than ribbon-like fettuccine.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the Veg-All, corn, celery, onion, mayonnaise, and cheddar, and put in an oven-proof casserole dish.
Crush the Ritz crackers and mix with the melted butter.
Sprinkle/spread the cracker mixture over the vegetable mixture and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until cracker mixture is lightly browned.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and sauce.
Cook in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 375° about 1 hour or until done.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Rinse berries in strainer and let towel dry on paper towels. Mix ingredients with berries and fill pie crust.
Dab with 2 tablespoons butter and cover with top crust.
Dab top crust with milk and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut slits on top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly and make into small balls. In double boiler, mix wax and chocolate chips. When melted, dip balls in mix. Place on wax paper until dry.

title: garlic and lemon chicken
directions: Rub chicken with lemon juice, then pour any remaining juice onto chicken. Combine olive oil, oregano, salt and pepper and brush chicken with mixture. Slice garlic and place on top of chicken.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Baste occasionally with oil/oregano mixture.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine drained vegetables,onion, cheese, mayonnaise and soup; mix well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 18-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer potatoes and onion.
Melt butter or margarine; stir in flour and cook until foamy. Gradually stir in chicken broth and mayo.
Cook until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Season and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine Karo syrup, sugar and water.
Stir and cook to hard ball.
Add peanuts and cook to golden brown (stir constantly and watch closely).
Set off fire.
Add baking soda, butter and vanilla and stir well.
Pour onto 2 buttered pans.
Spread out in center of pans.
Begin to pull from edges after 1 minute.
Pull thin and cool.

title: play dough
directions: If using food coloring, put droplets into measuring cup, then add water to make 1 cup.
Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and pulls away from sides of pan.
Put dough on wax paper and knead it until color is well blended.
Store play dough in airtight container.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain, then add all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste and simmer.

title: ninfa's green sauce
directions: Peel avocado and mash to a smooth pulp.
Add sour cream, milk, onion, garlic, cilantro, pepper sauce and lemon juice; blend with a wire whip.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving. Refrigerate any leftover sauce.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemonade until blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Divide between pie crust shells and chill.
Enjoy.

title: swirled chocolate and peanut butter souffle
directions: Grease the sides of a 2-quart souffle dish with margarine or butter.
For a collar on the souffle dish, measure enough foil to wrap around the top of the souffle dish and add 3 inches.
Fold the foil in thirds lengthwise.
Lightly grease 1 side with margarine or butter; sprinkle with sugar.
Attach the foil, sugar side in, around the outside of the dish so that the foil extends about 2 inches above the dish.
Take ends of foil together.
Sprinkle sides of dish with sugar.
Set the dish aside.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; Add all other ingredients.
Let stand in warm place for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut out.
Place in greased pans; let rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter or margarine.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and shortening.
Add eggs and food coloring; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together 3 times; add alternately with buttermilk and mix well.
Combine vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 layers at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly over crust.
Pour mixture over pecans. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or longer.
Makes 1 deep dish pie or 2 small pies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pile lightly in baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded American cheese over top.
Then top with one cup crushed potato chips.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fat-free fuzzy navel(for 1 serving))
directions: Combine ingredients in blender; blend on high setting, until smooth.
Pour in glass and enjoy!

title: eggplant puffs
directions: Drain and mash cooked eggplant.
Add egg, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Drop small amounts from teaspoon into hot deep fat.
Turn when brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Let chicken marinate for 2 to 3 hours or more, then cook on grill until done.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato sauce, water and chili powder.
Layer the following:
buttered tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
When all layered, pour 2/3 cup water around edge of dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.

title: "grandma maud's" apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
In large casserole dish, mix corn, eggs and corn bread mix.
Pour onion mix over corn mixture and stir well.
Dab sour cream on top and then top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dried bean soup
directions: Soak beans.
Add ham, ham bone or salt pork, boiling water, peppercorns, bay leaf and whole cloves.
Cook the soup slowly until the beans are soft, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
For the last 30 minutes, add carrot, celery with leaves, onion, sorrel, garlic, saffron and potatoes.
Remove and mince meat.
Put soup in food blender for several seconds.
Thin soup, if required with boiling water or milk.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°, in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.

title: punch
directions: Mix these ingredients, then add pineapple can full of water. You can also put in frozen strawberries.

title: party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Add sliced lemons and limes for added color and flavor. Just before serving, slowly drop the sherbet in by large spoonfuls. Serves approximately 25 people.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter; add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between the center of filling comes out clean.

title: frozen stew
directions: Combine beer, gravy mix and onion soup in crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients and push in pot until moistened.
Cook all day on low.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and saute onion and drain.
Stir in next ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Place, cut side down, around edge of casserole, then in the middle. Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef or venison stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Remove from pan.
Remove fat and bone from steak.
Cut into medium size chunks or strips.
Melt additional 2 tablespoons of butter in pan. Toss meat pieces in flour.
Coat thoroughly; brown in butter. Add salt and bouillon.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add mushrooms, onion and sour cream.
Heat.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: nutmeg sauce
directions: Mix sugars, flour, salt and nutmeg together.
Add 2 cups boiling water and cook until thick.
Add the butter; stir well and serve.

title: lemon heaven
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; let set, then whip.
Whip milk and sugar; add to jello mixture.
Whip to combine.
Line baking pan with cracker mixture, saving some crumbs to sprinkle on top of jello mixture.
Chill.

title: party punch
directions: Mix everything but 7-Up.
Place in a large container.
Stir a couple of times while freezing.
Punch should be thick and slushy. Stir in 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: crunchy munchers
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Combine the chocolate bits and peanut butter in a quart size glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and then add cereal and marshmallows.
Mix until all is evenly coated.
Pour into buttered pan.
Press evenly with back of spoon.
Refrigerate until set. Cut in squares.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in dish and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and stuffing.
Put in greased casserole. Pour melted margarine over top.
Spoon soup on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add shortening, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Stir, then add cold water, beaten eggs and yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make a dough just stiff enough to knead well (not too much).
Set aside to double in bulk, then pinch out dough to make a small biscuit as it will raise again while baking.
Butter top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thin pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt together; add flour and milk, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Batter will be thin; have skillet or griddle slightly greased and hot.
Pour enough batter to barely cover the bottom; tip and swirl the pan to spread the batter and keep the layer thin.
Turn as for hot cakes.

title: bran muffins(quick bread)
directions: Combine all-bran with boiling water. Let stand. Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Add all-bran mixture. Sift together soda, salt and flour. Add alternately with buttermilk. Add Bran Buds. Divide into 4 wide-mouth quart jars. Can be refrigerated 6 weeks. Do not stir when you take out needed portion. Bake in greased muffin tins 18 to 20 minutes at 400°. Makes approximately 72 muffins.

title: brown beef stock
directions: Heat pressure cooker.
Melt marrow; brown beef cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 15 minutes.
Let pressure drop on its own accord.
Strain.
Beef stock is used as the basis for many soups and sauces.
A clear broth or bouillon makes an appealing appetizer.

title: e-z chicken and dumplings
directions: Clean thoroughly and boil the chicken with salt and pepper. Skin and debone.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Remove 1 cup of chicken broth and combine with 1 can of cream of chicken soup. Using canned biscuits, add to remainder of chicken broth; do not cover.
Add soup after biscuits are done, then add chicken.
Heat until chicken is hot on very low heat.
These are not as good like Mamma used to make, but quick for a working couple.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add pinto beans, eggs and coconut.
Mix well.
Put into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: brer rabbit brown bread
directions: Put all-bran, raisins, oleo and molasses into bowl.
Add boiling water; stir until shortening is melted.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon; stir only to combine.
Fill 3 greased Campbell's tomato soup cans 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Moist.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and bone.
Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken until just tender; drain when done.
Saute onions and celery until glazed; add to spaghetti with all the rest of mix.
Place in baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Cook with top or foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Makes a big batch and can be frozen and baked later.
Don't put cheese on it if you want to freeze.
Wait until ready to bake when thawed.
Serves about 10 to 12 people.

title: no cook fudge frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add margarine, boiling water and vanilla.
Beat with mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Cool for 20 minutes or until you can spread.
Yields enough for the top and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake layers.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Save 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine rest of mix, butter and 1 egg. Mix
well
and pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at
350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, 2 eggs, peel and the salt.
Pour over baked layer.
Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: picante chicken
directions: Cook white rice.
Fry chicken (as for fried chicken).
Remove chicken.
Leave oil and drippings in pan.
Add picante sauce. Heat until sauce forms.
Place rice on platter, then chicken pieces on top and pour sauce/gravy over chicken.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread coconut evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Prepare cake mix following package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Combine cream cheese and melted butter in medium bowl.
Beat at low speed until creamy.
Add confectioners sugar. Beat until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake batter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely.
To serve, cut into individual pieces.
Turn upside down on plate to serve.

title: hearty chicken stroganoff
directions: Cook Noodles using the package directions; drain well, cover to keep warm.

title: super hot wings(deep frying)
directions: Thaw frozen wings completely and place into basket.
Pour 1 gallon of grease into 10 1/2-quart pot and bring temperature to 350°.
Slowly place basket of wings into grease and cook 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove; drain wings and pour into bowl.
Mix hot sauce with melted margarine and garlic salt.
Pour over wings and serve.

title: chocolate angel cake
directions: Place cake on a plate right side up.
With a small knife, cut along the outside edge of cake (about 1/2 inch from the edge).
Do not cut through to the bottom of cake, but almost.
Repeat, cutting along inside hole of cake, about a 1/2 inch from the edge.
Pull loose cake from the middle of cake, creating a "tunnel."
Set cake pieces aside.
In a small bowl, combine the pudding mix and half the container of Cool Whip.
Mix with cake pieces.
Fill up tunnel of cake with pudding mixture (there will be some leftover).
Turn cake over and frost with the rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In a soup pot, cook the beef slowly until meat loses its red color.
Add beef bouillon and remaining ingredients except rice. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer about 45 minutes. Cook and drain rice and add to mixture.
Simmer a few minutes more.
You can add 1 can of chopped tomatoes and adjust bouillon if desired.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Add salt to egg whites, beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until smooth and glossy.
Slowly add Karo beating until firmly peaked.
Fold in vanilla.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Wash chicken and wipe dry; set aside.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add chicken to mixture; coat well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple dessert
directions: Fill 2 quart casserole with sliced apples.
Pour over apples the margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Crumble together remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples; bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pecan paralines
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Until lightly brown.

title: cherry, banana, pineapple whip
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: pizza cups
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Spray muffin cups.
Place a biscuit in each cup (press to cover all of cup). Place 1 tablespoon Monterey Jack cheese in each cup.
Top with heaping tablespoon of meat.
Top with 1 tablespoon Mozzarella cheese.
Garnish with green onions, olives, mushrooms and green pepper.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: triple fudge pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour (until toothpick comes out clean).
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yummy!

title: no fat lemon blintz pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In blender or food processor, place egg whites, liquid egg substitute, sugar and vanilla.
Blend 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt, lemon juice, lemon peel, sour cream and flour. Blend thoroughly for a few seconds.
Gradually add and blend in cottage cheese.
Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour in mixture.
(Be sure it is a big pie plate, the stuff expands.)
Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the pie comes out clean.
The center of the pie will fall as it cools.
This is normal.
Use sugar substitute if diabetic.

title: cheesy salsa dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain any grease.
Add salsa and Velveeta. Simmer and stir until all cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: reese's brownie candies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 foil liners in muffin pans. Combine brownie mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Fill each liner with 2 tablespoonfuls of batter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Push 1 peanut butter cup in center of each cupcake until top is even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Cool!

title: hamburger cheese noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed, drain and set aside.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender (set aside).
Brown meat and sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine softened cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
Mix well.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Take 1/2 of the noodles and put them in the casserole dish.
Layer cheese mixture next then put remaining noodles over cheese mixture.
Pour melted butter over this.
Top with the meat mixture.
Heat
in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin crunch dessert
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, spices and eggs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Shake dry cake mix over pumpkin, press in nuts, spoon melted margarine over nuts evenly. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Invert when cool.
Top with Cool Whip, sprinkle nuts on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: batter buns
directions: Measure water into mixer bowl.
Add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg and 1 cup flour.
Combine with mixer on low speed, guiding batter into beaters with rubber scraper. Add remaining flour; beat with scraper until smooth.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling each a scant 1/2 full.
Let rise in warm place until batter reaches top of muffin cups, 30 to 40 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 buns.

title: shrimp and scallops in garlic butter
directions: Place butter in custard cup.
Microwave at High for 30 to 45 seconds until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes. Place shrimp in 9 or 10-inch diameter dish.
Pour butter mixture evenly over shrimp.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes, until shrimp are opaque, stirring every 2 minutes. Let stand, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted; add vanilla.
Stir and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook and mash eggplant.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake in moderate oven until firm.

title: southwestern dip
directions: Brown meat and add taco mix, water and refried beans.
Heat 5 minutes.
Spread beef and bean mixture in dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: slow cooker venison
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and add onions, bell peppers and garlic to grease; stir until done.
Season venison with salt, pepper and garlic salt and rub thoroughly with Worcestershire sauce.
Brown meat in pot with onions and bell peppers.
After meat is brown, add wine, one cup of water and crumbled bacon.
Cook in slow cooker (medium setting) for about 5 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
Great with white beans.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with frozen potato puffs. Bake, uncovered, at 370° for 35 minutes or until puffs are brown. Serves 4.

title: potato quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, chopping onion and green pepper first. Place into a greased baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: great chicken salad
directions: Gently add the chicken broth to the mayonnaise.
Lightly toss together chicken, celery, olives, pecans and salt.
Add broth and mayonnaise dressing; chill.

title: a moist and nutritious meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill for 1 hour or more.
Unmold into a shallow baking pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: sausage egg brunch
directions: Place bread pieces on bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (8 x 12-inch).
Place sausage on top of bread and sprinkle with cheese.

title: apricot jello
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Let cool and refrigerate until syrupy.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with apricot and pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Beat until smooth and fold in nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornmeal dumplin's
directions: Mix this
together
in	a
bowl and pour in just enough boiling water to make a fairly stiff dough.
Wad in small flat pones and drop on top
of
cooked
turnip
greens.	Cover
and simmer.

title: pizza canapes
directions: Brown and chop fine the sausage; drain off grease.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Melt cheeses in double boiler.
Mix with pork sausage mixture.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Spread 1 teaspoon on slice of rye and arrange on cookie sheet. Continue until topping is used up.
Top each with Italian seasoning.
Broil about 3 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Watch closely.
Can be frozen and then cooked.
Thaw 10 minutes before broiling.

title: hard candy(cinnamon)
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, very cautiously, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet, topped with powdered sugar.
Cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes more than two pounds.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and stir until thick with flour. Use as much as needed.
Add remainder of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with either sauce or whipped cream.

title: batter for deep frying
directions: Set baking powder aside.
Combine all ingredients adding milk slowly until desired thickness for item to be fried.
Add baking powder and mix in just before frying.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut biscuits in half.
Roll in mixture of sugars and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Place biscuits in pan.
Mix together remaining cinnamon and pecans. Melt oleo and pour over biscuits.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grande bean casserole
directions: Dice the onion and fry with the meat until the red is gone from meat.
Stir all ingredients together in a casserole dish and bake in the oven 20 minutes at 300°.
(You will love this dish.)

title: baked beans
directions: Simmer bacon, onion and green pepper in skillet for about 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir all together. Pour in casserole and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: variety cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato soup with ham
directions: In large cooking pot, add all ingredients, except potatoes and milk. Cook on low heat for about 1 hour, until tender. If chicken broth doesn't cover the vegetables, add water to cover tops of the vegetables. When tender, add potatoes and milk. Stir and simmer on low until potatoes are done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower vegetable dish
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed and set aside.
Blend soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine vegetables and soup mixture in large casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle French fried onion rings on top and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Coconut Crust:
Mix together coconut, melted oleo, sugar and vanilla cookies, crumbled.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° until light colored.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Set oven at 350° and preheat.
Mix cake mix and flour in bowl. Add eggs and mix, then add oil.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add chips and mix well.
Take teaspoon; bunch and roll into ball.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Take fork and press down.
Let cook until it becomes brown around edges or lightly brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain frozen vegetables.
(You can use fresh vegetables also.)
Add cheese.
Top with Ritz crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake in floured and greased tube pan for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef in a 2-quart casserole; cook on High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Drain off fat.
Add beans, tomato sauce, enchilada sauce, Cheddar cheese and onion.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan on top of stove. Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and oats.
Stir until well blended.
Roll out wax paper and drop by teaspoonfuls.
Eat when cool.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in one cup of water.
Put lemon extract in.
Beat egg yolks to the other 1/2 cup of water. Beat and then add to the water that is in the pan.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Take off burner.
Add 1/4 lemon juice and butter.
Beat until butter is melted.
Pour in baked pie crust. Add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stands in a peak.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of sugar to egg white.
Pour on pie. Brown in oven.
Bake at 440°.

title: green beans and swiss
directions: Stir margarine, flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add sour cream until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add beans.
Sprinkle on cheese, then crumbs, then pour on melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop finely and combine green pepper, cucumber and tomato. Chill.
Combine all other ingredients in pitcher and chill for at least 4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and noodles and drain.
Cool chicken and cut up. Mix mushroom soup with approximately 1 can of milk.
Add chicken, drained peas, noodles and seasoned salt.
Put in casserole dish and cover with crescent rolls.
Bake until rolls are brown.

title: whiskey butter sauce
directions: In a pan add garlic, shallots and whiskey.
Carefully place over the flame and cook until reduced by 3/4.
Allow the flames to die down.
Remove the pan from the heat, and start whisking in butter piece by piece.
Return the pan to the heat every so often to heat the mixture slightly.
Continue until all the butter is added and the mixture is emulsified.

title: date cake
directions: Put dates in hot water.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat eggs until fluffy and add to cream mixture.
Sift flour, soda, salt and add to cream mixture.
Add date mixture, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Boil ribs until very tender; cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake until brown.

title: 7-layer banana split cake
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and sugar.
Pack mixture firmly into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients (except carrots).
Heat until sauce is well blended.
Cook about 7 minutes.
Add carrots, which have been drained.
Marinate overnight.
Heat before serving.

title: sweet smelling potpourri
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Cover with heated white vinegar.
Let set for about a week.
Use like simmering potpourri that you would buy in a store.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: Cut together with knives until like peas in size.
Sprinkle ice water gradually, just enough to hold it together and soft enough to roll out.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle flour on rolling surface.
Roll thin as you like, turning over once.
Place in pie pan, pressing down around inside.
Cut off excess around edge and crimp with fingers.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat until browned.
While meat is browning, mix cornbread mix according to directions on package.
Drain grease from meat.
Add Ranch Style beans and picante sauce.
Mix well. Pour into oven-safe or microwave dish.
Layer cheese on top of meat mixture.
Pour cornbread batter on top of cheese.
Cook in uncovered dish until brown at 350° (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).

title: curry pork stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a roasting pan.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are cooked.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain. Cover bottom of roasting pan with thin sliced raw potatoes.
Cover with hamburger mixture.
Cover with a jar of pizza sauce and a can of cheese soup.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake!
Put as much in each layer as you like, according to how many people you are serving.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll in balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and condensed milk.
Fold in chocolate syrup to taste and pour into crust.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips or sprinkles.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a pot for one minute. Remove from heat.
Mix peanut butter, oats and vanilla into the heated mixture.
Place on tinfoil in balls or flattened shapes to dry.
Cool before eating, about 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together butter and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time. Add brown sugar. Sift flour and baking powder. Add to other mixture, alternating with milk. Bake at 325° in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy fresh fruit pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry shell. Set aside.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple juice, flour, sugar, vinegar and egg in saucepan. Cook until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make stuffing according to package directions and set aside.
