Cut breasts into halves and put on bottom of greased casserole (9 x 9-inch). Add 1 slice Swiss cheese on top of each chicken piece.
Pour combined mixture of soup and sour cream over chicken and cheese.
Top with dressing and bake for one hour (1/4 cup wine may be added to soup/sour cream mixture.

title: hawaiian macaroni salad
directions: Separate fruit from the juice; save both.
While cooking the macaroni, prepare the fruit sauce.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, eggs, and fruit juices in a saucepan.
Once sauce come to a boil, remove from heat.
The sauce will thicken as it cools.
Mix the sauce and cooked macaroni and allow it to cool in the fridge for 4 hours or overnight.
Then fold in whipped topping and marshmallows, and fruit.
Chill until ready to serve, This makes about 6 quarts. Very good.

title: gingerich special
directions: Cook potatoes in water, when partly done add macaroni and wieners.
Cook until almost done.
Add milk and cheese.
If too dry add more milk.
Simple and delicious.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, sugar, salt, pepper, cider vinegar, brown mustard and flour together.
Add potatoes and celery.
Serve hot or cold.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken together.
Layer chicken in tinfoil in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Can be baked at 325° in a sauce or barbecued.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in evaporated milk poured into a bowl.
Roll chicken in corn flakes.
Put chicken in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 to 2 hours or until tender in a 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop pecans and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Roll the cheese ball in chopped pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat brown sugar, butter, baking soda, cinnamon and salt until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, applesauce and eggs; beat until blended.
With a spoon, stir in raisins and chopped nuts.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan; cool completely.
When cake is cool, prepare glaze.

title: peach pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Put 2 tablespoons of flour and 2 tablespoons of sugar, mixed and pour over crust.
Then place 2 1/2 cans of drained peaches over that.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, some nutmeg and butter.
Then pour 1 small can Pet milk over pie and bake about 1 hour.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Place in layers on large plate.
Serve with taco chips.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Cut
potatoes,	carrots,
tomatoes
and onions in small pieces.
Add green	beans
and
corn.
Place meat in pot along with tomato sauce.	Add
water to about 3 or 4 inches from top of pot.
Salt and
pepper
to taste.
Cook on high for about 2 hours. Then add noodles and cook for 30 more minutes.

title: refrigerator raspberry pie
directions: Melt butter.
Combine with crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Pat buttered crumbs evenly over sides and bottom of pie plate and chill.

title: chicken stir-fry on rice
directions: Bring water and salt to boil in a covered medium size saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand. Stir cornstarch, soy sauce, sesame oil and broth in a bowl until blended.
Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large, deep nonstick skillet over high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry 1 minute, until chicken starts to brown.
Stir in vegetables and green onion; cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are hot and chicken is cooked through.
Stir cornstarch mixture again.
Pour into skillet and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and clear.
Spoon over rice.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water; save broth.
Remove chicken breasts when tender.
Take meat off bone; set aside.
Cook vermicelli; drain.
Add first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Can be made ahead, stored in fridge and baked right before serving.

title: pizza lover's lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Rinse with hot water; drain.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers until they are fine crumbs.
Mix crumbs with sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Dissolve corn syrup in whisky and add to the dry ingredients.
Mix well to blend.
The mixture must be moist enough to hold together.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: gruyere ring(prep time: 15 minutes; cooking time: 50 to 60 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat milk and butter to rolling boil in 2-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat and add wine.
Stir in flour with a large heat resistant spatula or spoon.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute; remove from heat. Beat in all 4 eggs at once; continue beating until smooth.
Fold in 2/3 cup of Gruyere cheese.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet to form an 8-inch ring; smooth with spatula.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until puffed and golden, 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Shake into walnut size balls.
Place on a rack on a cookie sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: mashed potato balls
directions: Mix cold mashed potatoes with beaten egg yolk, salt and pepper to taste.
Shape mixture into balls. Place in greased pan.
Make a dent in the top of each ball.
Put a pat of butter in each dent. Brown in the oven (400° to 450°).

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Put strawberries in food processor or blender.
Blend until fruit is pureed.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade until melted.
Add cranberry juice cocktail, cold water and strawberry puree.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Makes about 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: baked fish with stuffed dates
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cover bottom of a large baking pan with onion slices; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine rice, almonds, sugar, pepper, 1 teaspoon ginger root and dates.
Stir well to blend.
Fill stomach of cleaned fish with rice mixture. Close opening and secure with toothpicks.
Place stuffed fish on top of onion slices in pan.
Add water.
Rub top of fish with remaining ginger.
Cover pan with foil, sealing tightly around edges.
Bake 45 minutes for bluefish or 30 minutes for porgies. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Place peaches in bottom of pan.
Top with flour, sugar, baking powder and milk that has been mixed well.
Top with peach juice.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add softened gelatin, salt and lemon juice; chill.
When mixture begins to congeal, divide into halves.
Add cubed, unpeeled apple to one part.
Half-fill mold and chill.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes, add oleo, salt and pepper, soup, Cheddar cheese, chopped onion and sour cream.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with corn flakes and butter, if desired.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar, then add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add buttermilk (1/2 cup) with teaspoon of soda; set aside.
Mix nuts, dates and candy in the flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, with 1 cup of buttermilk.
Now, add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in tube pan and cook 50 to 60 minutes at 325° until done.
When done, pour filling over cake.

title: jello and ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in ice cream until melted. Chill until very thick.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into crust. Chill until firm.
Garnish with more berries.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
(Cheese may be mixed in or sprinkled on top.) Turn into a greased 2-quart oblong Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baby carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 -14 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in thawed strawberries, pecans, bananas and pineapple.
Put half of mixture in dish and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.
Leave other half at room temperature.
Gently spread sour cream over refrigerated half; add the remaining mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble
cornbread
in
large
container.
Pour
enough broth over
cornbread
until
moist.
Dissolve
bread
in hot water. Add to cornbread mixture.
Cook onions in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and add to mixture.
Add slightly beaten eggs to milk; combine with cornbread mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake
at
350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown and middle is firm.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and 1 egg together.
Pour into pan of melted margarine; spread.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs; pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: great icing
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: In small bowl, whisk together well egg, milk and sour cream. In large bowl, sift together flour, salt, mace, sugar and baking powder.
Pour liquids into well in drys and beat well with eggbeater or whisk.
Add butter and stir until mixed.
Fold in blueberries.
Drop batter by large spoonfuls onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Brown on one side.
Turn and brown on other side. Turn only once.
Yields 1 dozen pancakes.

title: libby's spaghetti creole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onions and green pepper in bacon fat.
Fry Libby's chopped beef until crisp and brown and add remaining ingredients.
When mixture starts to simmer, season to taste.
Cook a few minutes longer and serve with grated cheese.

title: dip
directions: Brown ground chuck, sausage, chilies and onion; drain.
Cube the Velveeta cheese; add and melt.
Cut up tomatoes; drain.
Add juice and garlic.
Serve with tortilla chips or potato chips.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend the flour, powdered sugar and butter; then spread in greased pan up to the edges. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size chunks after cooled.
Add remaining items and thoroughly mix together.
Chill.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water and stir well.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Fold into Jell-O.
Add oranges, grapes and coconut.
Mix together.
Pour into a 6 x 10-inch pan.
Let set until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chili for 100(approximately 16 gallons)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer all afternoon.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain while hot. Add Accent, seasoned salt, lemon juice and oil. Mix and marinate overnight, then add pimento, green pepper, green onions, celery, olives and mayonnaise. Toss well. Let stand for at least 2 hours before serving. Will keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: yummy fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Continue stirring.
Take off heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate bits and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered platter.
Let cool and cut.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apple, raisins, pecans and grapes in large bowl and toss with enough mayonnaise to coat the fruit.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each cone.
Set cones on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine strawberry jam and sour cream; add jam mixture with flour; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Divide in floured pans and greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: pasta salad
directions: Clean and peel carrots.
Clean mushrooms; slice all vegetables and steam until soft.
Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain pasta in colander and rinse with cold water to cool quickly. Drain thoroughly and place in large bowl.
Add vegetables and stir.
Add Italian dressing and gently stir until covered. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serves a lot.
Great for road trips or pre-game meals.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and salt in water until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Mix well and pour into greased 1-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: baked spinach
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems.
Steam in large saucepan on high for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Squeeze out as much water as possible.
Chop coarsely.
Saute mushrooms in skillet. Add tomatoes, garlic, onions, parsley, thyme and nutmeg.
Simmer on high for 5 minutes, until juices have thickened.
Spread spinach over bottom of lightly buttered, shallow, 8 or 9-inch tart pan or square oven-to-table pan.
Spread tomato mixture over center, allowing some of the green to show around edges.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated.

title: walking taco salad
directions: In a medium size bowl mix together picante sauce, refried beans, taco seasoning mix, mayo and sour cream.
Spread onto pizza pan.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Mix applesauce, butter, egg yolks, sugar and nutmeg.
Add milk.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° until custard is firm.
Top with meringue.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Slowly add milk; mix well and pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: crab-broccoli macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni.
Saute onions and garlic in pan coated with vegetable spray.
Remove and set aside.
Melt margarine in pan; add flour.
Gradually stir in wine.
Cook until mixture thickens. Remove.
Gradually stir in milk, basil and dill weed.
Add onion mixture, pepper, broccoli and crabmeat to sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine pasta.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Cook cheese and sausage until cheese melts.
Mix in flour. Roll in small balls and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: steamed vegetable medley
directions: Place sliced carrots, green pepper strips and sliced squash in steaming rack.
Place rack over boiling water; cover and steam 3 to 5 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Transfer vegetables to serving dish.
Add butter, lemon juice, salt and pepper; toss gently.
Sprinkle with chives.
Yields 2 servings.

title: easy ground turkey burgers
directions: Brown onion in frying pan.
Once onion is brown, combine the onion with the ground turkey, egg and bread crumbs.
Shape the ground turkey into 4 patties.
Brown on both sides.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water; add melted margarine and flour.
Stir quickly (mixture will get thick).
Let cool.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating each into dough with a spoon.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix cheese with a little of the milk.
Add pudding and rest of milk.
Beat until thick.
Spoon into baked shell from above.
Spread 8 ounces Cool Whip over top.
Drizzle with one package hot fudge or some other type of chocolate topping.
(Hershey's topping in the squeeze bottle works well.)

title: bean chalupa
directions: Place beans, pork roast, water, onions, garlic, chilies and pimentos in a heavy kettle. Cover and simmer about 5 hours or until tender.
Remove roast and break up with a fork.
Return to pot. Cook, uncovered, about 1/2 hour until thick.
Serve over corn chips.
Condiments:
Diced tomatoes, diced avocado, diced onions, grated Cheddar cheese, hot pepper sauce or taco sauce.
Good!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: waldorf-astoria cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, coloring, vanilla and 2/3 cup buttermilk.
Blend well. Add eggs and rest of milk.
Beat 1 minute by mixer.
Mix vinegar and soda to cake and blend by hand.
Bake in loaf or layers at 350°.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine bread, milk, eggs, 2 tablespoons catsup and mustard.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add beef, sausage, onion and parsley; mix well.
Divide mixture into 4 equal parts.
Pack one meat portion into each of two ungreased loaf pans.
Place 1/2 of the cheese into each pan; cover each with a second portion of meat mixture, packing over cheese.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Lightly beat egg.
Add milk or water and mix.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add egg and milk (for heavier batter, use more milk).
Drop by spoonfuls into hot chicken gravy; cook for 20 minutes.
Do not remove lid or move boiler.

title: savory salmon
directions: Place filet in foil and form a pocket.
Put seasonings on to taste.
Spread top with mayo and put lemon juice on bottom until bottom is covered.
Close foil tight and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 min.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots about 20 minutes and drain.
Let cool.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate at least 24 hours before serving.
Carrots will keep at least 2 weeks.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain and put into greased casserole.
Saute onions and peppers in small amount of fat, add meat and brown. Add soup, milk, salt, and pepper to meat mixture.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: fresh corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart rectangular casserole. Puree 1 cup corn with melted butter and eggs in blender or food processor.
Mix remaining ingredients in medium bowl and add pureed mixture and blend well.
Pour into casserole and bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in milk in top of double boiler.
Chop tomatoes and peppers fine; add to cheese and serve.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and dash pepper.
Add chicken broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir in cream and wine.
Place broccoli crosswise in 12-inch by 8-inch by 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over.
Top with chicken.
To remaining sauce, add cheese; pour over chicken; sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or till hot; then broil till golden, about 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Coat chicken breasts with mustard, then dip into crumb mixture.
Place breaded chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon, celery, onion and potatoes until tender.
You can add a little oleo if necessary.
Cover with water and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Simmer until done and vegetables are tender.
Add milk and cheese and simmer until the cheese melts. Serves 4.
This is a favorite winter lunch at our house.

title: caramel candy bars(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat candies and milk in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring often until smooth; remove from heat.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in large bowl.
Stir in margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of crumbly mixture in pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: microwave hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in deep 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole dish.
Heat, uncovered, on simmer for 5 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Stir once.
Heat an additional 4 1/2 minutes on simmer.
Serve very hot with crisp corn chips for dipping. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peggy's easy chocolate mousse
directions: In electric blender, combine chocolate chips, sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs.
Heat milk to scalding point.
Pour hot milk into blender.
Cover and blend for 1 minute.
Pour into 4 cups and chill until set.
Garnish with whipped cream.
This is very rich and makes 8 good-sized servings.

title: baked fruit wonder
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Put bits of margarine into batter.
Pour juicy fruit over top and spread evenly and bake 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: caramel ice cream
directions: Put sugar and 1/2 cup water in a heavy skillet and stir over heat until the mixture is a deep golden brown.
The deeper the color the more caramel flavor the syrup has.
Remove from heat and add remaining 1/4 cup boiling water slowly while stirring.	Let mixture cool slightly.

title: overnight salad
directions: Using a shallow glass bowl, layer vegetables, except tomato, in given order.
Spread mayonnaise over top and tightly to edges to seal.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, season with garlic powder, sprinkle with cheese and spread tomato over top.
Do not toss.
Serve layered.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water.
Drain liquid to make 1/2 cup and mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: In heavy 1-quart saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine.
Remove from heat.
With wire whisk or fork, beat in sugar and milk until smooth and easy to spread.
Makes enough to ice one 9-inch single layer cake.

title: five-bean soup(low-fat)
directions: Combine beans.
Divide into four equal parts, about 3 3/4 cups each.
To make one batch, wash one batch of beans.
Place in large kettle, add enough water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Drain and rinse beans.
Return to kettle.
Add spices and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove spices.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
One cup equals 191 calories and 1 g fat.

title: sausage dip(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Brown sausage, onion and garlic until very brown.
Pour off grease.
Blend together soft cream cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes until smooth.
Add meat to cream cheese and Ro-Tel mix.
Pour in baking dish; cover and warm in microwave until hot.
Heat tortilla chips in 250° oven for 10 minutes.
Absolutely divine!

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix and put in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy cole slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion and apple.
Season to taste. Stir in mayonnaise to your desired consistency.

title: cashew noodles
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
Saute last 3 ingredients until onion is clear.
Add vegetables to mixture in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Save part of the noodles to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: jambalaya
directions: In an electric skillet at 325° melt butter.
Add garlic and onion.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add green pepper, seasonings and canned tomatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add ham, shrimp, broth and rice. Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to 250° and cook 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is tender.

title: slow and easy chicken
directions: Place breast pieces in baking pan.
Mix sour cream and soup (undiluted). Spread over chicken.
Bake at 275° about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: potatoes you will love
directions: Mix together except the cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle cheese over top in last 15 minutes.
Cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff sandwiches
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Wrap in foil and heat in 375° oven 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown beef with onion; drain off excess fat.
Stir in sour cream, milk, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat, but to not let boil.
Spread meat mixture over cut surface of bread.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place on baking sheet and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If desired, use some coconut and cherries to decorate.
Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour once with soda and salt.
Cream shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and mix until smooth.
Add peanut butter; stir well, then add flour mixture.
Mix to a stiff batter, then add vanilla.
Form into tiny balls and press onto a greased 10 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make a waffle design.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from pan to cake cooler immediately after baking.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: baked chicken in sherry sauce
directions: Salt and pepper chicken in flour.
Brown butter.
Then place in baking dish.
Pour off half of the dripping.
Saute onion in same skillet.
Add soup, wine and milk.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Chop peppers.
Add all ingredients; mix well. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gwen's salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all together in blender until smooth (add cheese gradually).
Put in 10-inch glass pie plate and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Refrigerate after cooled.
Garnish with crushed drained pineapple, cherries or blueberries, after cooling.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Pour in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Keep mixture hot in oven.

title: aunt joyce's brickle crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with crackers, packing tightly.
In medium size saucepan, melt butter, then add sugar and boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir a lot. Immediately pour over crackers and bake for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle the chocolate and peanut butter bits over crackers.
Use the back of a spoon and spread evenly as they melt.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Break into pieces and serve.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheets an bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add all ingredients except noodles. Simmer together 30 minutes.
Add noodles and simmer 25 minutes more.
If you want more of a stew consistency, use only 1/2 the beef broth.

title: country-style ribs
directions: Simmer ribs, covered, in salted water that just covers ribs for about 1 hour.
Use large kettle.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Pour over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Pack firmly into tube cake pan.
Refrigerate several days.
Unmold.	Keep refrigerated.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and blueberries.
Put in bottom of pie crust.
Pour hot Cream Filling over berries and top with Meringue.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers
and
pack
into 6 hot sterilized quart jars. To
each
jar
add
2 teaspoons dill seed, 1/8 teaspoon instant minced
garlic,
1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper and 1 slice onion.
For
a
stronger garlic flavor, use 1/4 teaspoon instant minced garlic in each jar.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring
to
a
boil; pour boiling hot over cucumbers, leaving 1/4-inch head space.
Seal at once.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: overnight hamburger buns(makes about 20 buns)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: meat balls by monahan
directions: You will need a 4-quart saucepan, 1 large mixing bowl and 1 small mixing bowl.

title: noodles from scratch
directions: Combine beaten eggs and salt.
Add flour gradually, until dough forms.
Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes.
Roll out dough and cut noodles.
Serves 6.

title: lazy day
directions: Mix together and sprinkle over 1 can apples or peaches.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: spaghetti chop-suey
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Clean the peppers, onions and celery.
Cut up peppers.
Add diced onions and celery.
Cover. Cook for 30 minutes.
Cooks in its own juices.
Add the crushed tomatoes, sugar, Italian seasoning, Mrs. Dash's original blend and sauteed garlic.
Continue to cook on low heat.
Fry hamburg until brown.
Add to sauce.
Cook until vegetables are done (not mushy). Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples and all ingredients until well coated.
Pour into pastry shell and top with pastry.
Brush top with milk; sprinkle a little sugar over top.
Bake at 400° until apples are soft and juice is thick.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, vanilla, margarine and sour cream.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl mix sugars, cinnamon and nuts.
Put half of the batter in a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle half the sugar mixture on the batter in the pan.
Add the other half sugar mixture to the remaining batter.
Pour remaining batter into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix cake and pudding mix.
Add all other ingredients, mixing after each.
Add chocolate chips last.
Stir lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt cake pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage lightly; drain off fat and set aside.
Whip eggs and milk together, then add the other ingredients.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; chill. Makes about 5 cups.

title: pesto fettuccini with chicken and vegetables
directions: Saut peppers and asparagus in oil about 10 minutes.
Put in bowl and add tomatoes (which have been softened in boiling water). Saut chicken until cooked (3 to 5 minutes).
Add to vegetables. Add half pesto and half Parmesan.
While vegetables are cooking, cook pasta in water.
Add remaining pesto and cheese to pasta in separate bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chicken and vegetables over pasta.

title: derby cheese torte
directions: Blend cheese and onion together.
Adding a small amount of mayonnaise will make it smoother. Add in nuts.
Place mixture in spring-form pan.

title: asparagus mold
directions: Boil sugar, salt, vinegar and 1 cup water.
Add lemon juice. Scrape about 1 teaspoon onion into sugar mixture.
Set aside to cool and to jell slightly.
Drain asparagus; cut water chestnuts and pimientos.
Place vegetables in mold and add liquid mixture. Chill several hours.

title: mississippi mud cake and icing
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Take out and cover with tiny marshmallows. Bake another 10 minutes. Cool and frost with the following icing.

title: perfection salad(salad for 50)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water about 5 minutes. Dissolve in hot water. Add sugar, salt, lemon juice and vinegar. Pour into large shallow pan. Chill. When it begins to thicken, add vegetables. Serve on piece of lettuce. Garnish with a little salad dressing.

title: western beef and rice casserole
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Brown beef in oil.
Remove beef from pan; add onion, celery, green pepper and rice.
Cook, stirring, until brown.
Add tomatoes, water, seasonings, beef and olives; bring to a boil.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; cover. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate and a little butter and put on top.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Can use lite Cool Whip and sugar-free pudding.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add frozen strawberries and mix until thawed.
Put in refrigerator for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put half of mixture in final pan and spread half of sour cream over.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture and top with remaining sour cream.

title: matt's dr. pepper ribs(refrigerate over night)
directions: Mix Dr.
Pepper, dressing and black pepper in a sealable plastic bag and add ribs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot-sour soup
directions: Soak mushrooms and lily buds in hot water for 30 minutes. Drain; cut off and discard tough stems.
Cut mushrooms into thin strips.
Cut lily buds in halves.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, molasses, then boiling water.
Add salt, soda and spices to flour.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: angel mysteries(shaped cookies)
directions: Put fruits, nuts and cereal through a food grinder.
Alternate them for thorough mixing.
Mix in coconut with ground mixture. Add pudding mix to corn syrup and lemon juice.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over ground mixture; mix lightly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen balls.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine 3 cups milk and pour over 2 eggs, beaten.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until golden brown on top.
Serve hot from baking dish, garnished if desired with parsley sprigs, pimiento strips and pepper rings.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cinnamon rice krispies treat
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Yield:
24 treats.

title: chicken sausage jambalaya
directions: Boil fryer in salt water.
Debone.
Save broth.
Fry deboned chicken until slightly brown.
Fry sausage and drain.
Add bell pepper and onions to sausage.
Mix all meats and vegetables together and cover with 1-inch of broth.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Cook 3/4 cup rice.
Mix rice with meat and vegetable mixture.
Place in large casserole and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
It is better made the day before and put in refrigerator so seasoning can set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter. Add powdered sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crusts and chill.

title: croutons
directions: Place bread on cookie sheet.
Brush both sides with mixture made from remaining ingredients.
Cut in cubes.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Wash unpeeled rhubarb and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt butter or margarine and stir in sugar. Spread over bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange rhubarb on top.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter over rhubarb to within 1/2-inch of top of dish.
Pour remaining batter into cupcake pans.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake is done.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes. Invert serving dish over top of cake pan and turn out cake. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired. Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn chowder
directions: Simmer the potatoes and onion in water until done.
Add the corn, milk and soup.
Fresh corn is really good.
In that case, you would have to cook it with potatoes and onion.
The crumbled bacon (fried) adds a lot of flavor.

title: hot lemony coffee
directions: Make coffee.
Pour
4 cups in a saucepan.
Stir in sugar and simmer until dissolved.
Add orange and lemon juices.
Stir in rind.
Pour coffee mixture into four cups.
Top with whipped cream.

title: frank and noodle supper
directions: Cut slits in franks, almost, but not quite all the way through, about every 1/2 inch.
When grilled, they will curl in a circle.
Place on a slice of bread and fill center with hot sauerkraut or beans.

title: fried tortillas with cheese
directions: Cut tortillas into 6 to 8 triangles.
Heat oil in a frying pan.
Drop tortilla sections and fry until golden brown.
Remove and drain.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Place tortillas on a cookie sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with strips of green pepper.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: pea and ham soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onions and garlic in the butter until tender, about 5 minutes. Add peas, stock, bay leaf and pepper. Heat to boiling and reduce heat. Add ham, cover and simmer for about two hours, stirring occasionally. Add carrots and potatoes, cover and simmer for a further 20-30 minutes. Serve with fresh bread.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; add the corn meal.
Beat the eggs; add milk and melted shortening.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into a greased baking pan and bake 35 minutes in a moderate oven at 400°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put tenderizer as directed on steak.
After alloted time of tenderizer, rinse steak.
Pat dry.
(I find if steak is placed in freezer for a while it slices better.)
Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Dice onion (I really like to add more onion.)
Brown beef and onion in margarine in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Can be kept on low heat until ready to serve.

title: rolled stuffed flank steak
directions: Score flank steak (make light cuts 1/4 to 1/2-inch across the surface of the meat).
Pound steak with edge of a heavy saucer or a meat pounder to flatten.
Mix onion, breadcrumbs, celery, olives, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly on one side of the steak, leaving an inch margin free of stuffing.
Roll steak, beginning at narrow end and tie with string or fasten with skewers.
Brown meat roll in hot fat.
Add bouillon or water, cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
(Meat may be cooked, covered, in a 325° oven for the same length of time.)

title: apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sift together flour, sugar, brown, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat together eggs, oil, applesauce, milk and flavorings.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pain perdu
directions: Heat the oil in a large heavy skillet.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, liqueur, milk, sugar and lemon zest and whisk together until eggs are frothy and sugar is dissolved.
When oil is hot, dip bread to coat well on both sides.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Drain off
all juices.	Add fruit to Cool Whip.
Chill. Great Lenten dish.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, soy sauce and pepper.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meat balls in shortening in 12-inch skillet.
Drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly until jelly is melted.
Add meat balls and stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, 50 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add flour, salt, sugar, paprika, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder which have been mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Add remaining water and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, peas and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: aunt jenny's brown rim cookies
directions: Combine margarine, shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar, then beaten eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheets.
Let stand a few minutes, then flatten cookies by stamping with the bottom of a glass covered with a damp cloth.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until rims are lightly browned.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, celery, green pepper and onions together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for one hour.

title: clam fritters
directions: Beat eggs, add salt, flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add ground clams and mix thoroughly.
Add cracker crumbs just before cooking so they stay crisp.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat condensed milk and pudding mix until well blended.
Gradually add water and beat until smooth. Chill at least 1 hour. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into cool pastry shell and chill thoroughly.

title: cheesy chicken marsala
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, parsley and paprika in a plate. Press each chicken breast in crumb mixture on both sides. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put breasts in. Sprinkle chicken with remaining crumbs. Dot butter over tops of chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour wine over chicken and bake 15 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.
Serve with spaghetti and sauce and good salad. Yum! Serves 4 to 6. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix vegetable oil, eggs, white sugar and brown sugar together. Add all at once remaining ingredients.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
No frosting is needed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in baking dish.
Blend butter, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Work until crumbly, then pack tightly over apples.
(If apples are dry, add 1 tablespoon water to them.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: berries and cream dessert
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Fold in berries and Cool Whip. Split ladyfingers and line oblong dish.
Pour berry mixture over ladyfingers.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: marbled brownies
directions: In small bowl at medium speed, beat cream cheese and add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg, 2 tablespoons flour and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla. Blend on high and beat until smooth.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter delite
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to a full boil for 1 minute.
Add salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drip onto wax paper by spoonfuls, working quickly.
Let set 15 minutes to 1 hour before removing.
Store in sealed container.

title: sweet and sour baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Mix in a medium size saucepan all ingredients except chicken. Bring to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened. In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken. Bake 30 minutes. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake an additional 30 minutes, basting occasionally, until chicken is tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain and add taco seasoning mix and kidney beans.
Stir well.
Let cool completely.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes in large bowl.
Add beef mixture and Doritos (crushed). Toss with Thousand Island dressing.

title: stuffed peppers 3
directions: Cut tops off peppers and scoop out all the seeds and pulp. Put into boiling water until they start getting soft.
Drain the peppers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until puffed up and brown on top.

title: corn meal stuffing
directions: Put the chicken broth in pan and heat until boiling.
Add the corn meal slowly while stirring.
Cook for about 10 minutes and then add the bread crumbs, egg, celery and onion.
Add the salt, pepper, sage and other seasonings to taste.
Mix well.
Stuff bird.

title: meatballs hawaiian
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add hamburger, egg, 1/2 cup chopped onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Make balls; saute in 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove balls from pan.
Saute celery, pepper and 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Stir in pineapple, broth, vinegar, brown sugar and ginger; blend and stir into sauce of soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add meatballs to sauce and simmer in 350° oven.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve over pasta, salad greens or as a dip.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Chop zucchini and boil until half done.
Add onion, cheese, eggs and soup mixed with enough water left from boiling zucchini to give it some moisture.
Melt butter and mix with crumbs. Spread on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: In a small saucepan, bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Boil syrup for 1 minute.
Cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, juice and Cool Whip. Sprinkle in pudding mix. Add marshmallows and nuts. Stir together and refrigerate 12 hours or more.

title: herbed rice
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Dissolve beef granules in hot water.
Combine with other ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chunky chicken curry
directions: Place 3 chicken breasts on a microwave-safe plate, cover with plastic wrap and microcook on High power for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool; remove meat from bones and cut into chunks.

title: interesting salad
directions: Prepare the topping in a saucepan over low heat, by cooking together almonds, water and sugar until sugar melts or moisture is gone.
Pour onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: orange shrub punch
directions: Chill all juices and ginger ale.
Pour Hawaiian Punch into punch bowl.
Add cranberry juice cocktail.
Stir in ginger ale. Ladle sherbet in and allow to melt some before serving.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs and paprika and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until mixture is heated through and bubbly.
May be served in individual shells.
May also be served without cooking as a salad on lettuce leaves.
Drained, sliced water chestnuts or 1/4 cup slivered almonds may be added for crunchy goodness.
Serves 8.

title: pam's sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin gobs
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by tablespoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan cake fingers
directions: Beat egg whites (not
too dry) and fold in brown sugar; a flat spoon-type beater
is
almost
a must.
Add flour, salt and baking powder mixed
together
as	in
an angel food cake. Save
out
1/2 cup
of
flour
to	dredge	nuts.
Add
pecans, dredged, and flavoring.	Bake in a square or a tube pan, lined with
heavy greased
paper
at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove
the paper while warm.
You will be sure it won't work, but
it	will. Cut
into
fingers	when
cooled.
Ice
with a confectioners sugar icing.

title: pumpkin roll(yields 20 slices)
directions: Beat the eggs at high speed 5 minutes; gradually beat the sugar into eggs.

Add the pumpkin and lemon juice to the sugar mixture. Stir together the dry ingredients and add to the pumpkin mixture. Line 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet with waxed paper, then spread mixture on wax paper.
Top with 1 cup chopped pecans.
(This is important; the roll sticks together without the nuts.)
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Watch that edges don't get too brown.
Remove from oven and immediately remove the waxed paper.
Roll up in a towel as for jelly roll.
Let cool.

title: betty's cherry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread 3/4 of mixture in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over mixture.
Spoon remaining batter in "islands" over filling.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle thin powdered sugar icing over bars while still warm.

title: orange-cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce and water until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Gel until partially set.
Add nuts, oranges and sour cream.
Pour in a 2-quart mold and let set in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook or microwave spinach and drain very dry.
Pat with paper towels.
Mix all ingredients together.
Good with vegetables or crackers and chips, or large loaf of bread, scooped out and use bread as dipper.

title: peasant salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut tomatoes, cucumbers, yellow pepper and red onion into bite-sized pieces; place vegetables in large bowl.
Stir in chopped basil leaves, capers, garlic, olive oil, red wine vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cut bread into 1-inch pieces.
Add bread to vegetable mixture; toss gently to coat with dressing.
Top salad with olives.
Garnish with basil sprig.
Makes 12 accompaniment servings; about 220 calories per serving.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Put in a one-quart pitcher of ice water.

title: aunt soph's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in one egg at a time until lemon colored and thick.
Stir in part of flour; beat.
Stir in a little milk.
Stir in a little flour with the baking powder added, then beat in milk.
Add vanilla; beat.
Bake at 350° until middle springs back to touch (cupcakes at 400° for 15 minutes, loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or layer pans at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes).

title: fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple with juice in bowl; sprinkle dry pudding mix over this and mix.
Slice bananas and sprinkle a little lemon juice over bananas.
Put bananas and cherries in pudding mix. Keep in refrigerator.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Layer 1/2 the noodles, meat mixture, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marchetti
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 1/3 package of non-skid noodles as directed and add to hamburger. Then add the remaining ingredients (tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, cheese and garlic powder).
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan; add onion.
Cook a few minutes; add broccoli and cook until very tender (almost mushy). While broccoli is cooking, put one can of cream of mushroom soup in saucepan.
Add 1/2 soup can of water and 1/2 roll of garlic cheese, diced.
Heat soup until cheese melts.
Pour broccoli in baking dish, 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 6-inch; top with soup mixture. Spread buttered crumbs on top.
Sprinkle with paprika before baking at 350° until it bubbles around the sides.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Blend in flour, shaken smooth.
Add milk to saucepan and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place 2 to 3 cups cooked cut up potatoes in greased baking dish.
Add sauce mix.
Brown 1/2 cup dry bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle on potato mixture and bake 20 to 25 minutes (longer if refrigerated).
May be made ahead but adjust baking time.
Substitute broccoli, cauliflower or macaroni.
Good for buffet:
5 pounds potatoes plus 3 times the sauce plus 1 pound cheese serves 20 to 25.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Mash dates, pecans and cherries together using hands.
Add flour, baking powder, sugar, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly with hands and pour into 2 well-greased, floured brown paper-lined loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Cut meat into serving pieces and dust with flour, then pound flour into meat. Sprinkle salt, pepper, paprika and dry mustard on meat.

Heat oil and butter in a flameproof casserole until it foams. Add meat and brown on both sides. Add onion, garlic, water, soy sauce, brown sugar and sour cream. Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Use the sauce on potatoes or meat.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients and put in casserole.
Crush 2 cups corn flakes and mix with 1/4 cup melted margarine; spread this mixture over top of casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Pour measured flour onto a square of waxed paper.
Add salt and soda to flour; stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Dot top with additional cut up gumdrops, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chips and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with the chips. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy tuna garden wedges
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Pat dough in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with floured hands, forming 1/2-inch rim.
Bake until crust is light brown, about 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add extract and eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Chill.
Roll and cut into desired shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Cut crust from bread; butter.
Cut slices into 12 or 16 cubes. Line bottom of greased casserole dish with the bread.
Sprinkle with cheese, alternating bread and cheese until all is used, ending with layer of cheese on top.
Beat eggs and combine with milk and seasoning.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand 3 hours, but preferably overnight.
Cook next morning, uncovered, for breakfast. Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix
mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and refrigerate (the longer the better).
Mix just before serving so broccoli will stay fresh.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: whole grain low-fat buttermilk waffles
directions: Stir the first seven ingredients together with a fork.	Add buttermilk, egg and canola oil.
Grill on waffle iron, according to directions.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; stir well.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend until mixed well. Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: shoepeg corn relish
directions: Drain all cans of vegetables.
Combine rest of vegetables in large bowl.
Bring rest of ingredients to a boil or until sugar dissolves.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Store in refrigerator for months.
Makes about 3/4 gallon.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in a long pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on bottom.
Add remaining ingredients in layers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger lightly; drain off excess fat.
Add 1 can tomato sauce, oregano, brown sugar, vinegar, pizza sauce, salt and chili powder.
Simmer together 20 to 30 minutes.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat on low speed 1 minute.
Layer 1/3 of the pudding mix, half of the bananas and half of the wafers in 1 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining pudding.
Cover and chill.

title: festive corn salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve with lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: parmigiana chicken packets
directions: You will need 4 (12 x 8) sheets aluminum foil.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Layer in order given.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325°
oven.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook and drain frozen broccoli.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, broth and seasonings.
Layer broccoli, rice and chicken.
Pour creamed mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Drain olives thoroughly.
Put a good teaspoon of dough in palm and roll like a ball until the olive is covered.
Chill thoroughly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
These may be made before the party and frozen.
Bake at least 15 minutes if frozen.

title: potato-cheese braid
directions: Preparation:
In medium bowl, mix yeast, 3/4 cup of the flour, the salt, sugar and potato granules.

title: ragu sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook for 2 hours.
Keep stirring often. Will stick easy.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix well, form into a ball, refrigerate.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.
Pour cocktail sauce over ball before serving.

title: sweet crisp cucumber pickles
directions: First Day:
Wash and slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices of cucumbers.
Soak in lime water for 24 hours (1 cup lime to 7 pounds cucumbers and water to cover).
Do not use metal pan for soaking cucumbers.

title: cheese vegetable quiche
directions: Steam vegetables 5 minutes; place in pastry shell.
Top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring water to boil and add grits and salt.
Cook until thickened.
Add 1 stick margarine and 2/3 tube of cheese and cook until melted; remove from heat.
Break eggs in 1 cup measuring cup, finish filling with milk.
Beat eggs with fork and add to grits mixture.
Mix well and pour into a well buttered casserole. Dot with remaining cheese over the grits.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine; add corn flakes and sprinkle over grits mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy peanut dip
directions: In food processor or blender, combine
all
ingredients except half of scallions.
Process to a smooth
paste.
Transfer
to a serving bowl and garnish with
remaining
scallions. Serve with fried shrimp as an appetizer.

title: bulgogi(korean beef)
directions: Thoroughly mix sirloin with seasonings (and optional wine). Let marinate for at least 2 hours (mix occasionally).
Grill or pan-broil.

title: baked shells and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, bouillon cubes and mustard, stirring until thick.
Gradually add milk, stirring until sauce begins to boil.
Turn off stove and gradually add cheese slices.
Meanwhile, cook as directed Prince spaghetti shells. Combine shells and sauce in buttered casserole dish.
Melt butter in bowl and mix with bread crumbs.
Spread over shells and cheese casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange balls candy
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cream margarine and sugars together; add orange juice, wafers and pecans.
Form into balls and roll in flaked coconut.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and liquid separate and then blend together.
Cook in 2 pie pans in uncooked pie shells.

title: egg strata
directions: Cut crusts, butter both sides and place 6 slices in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Cook bacon; drain. Crumble.
Spoon half of mushrooms, onions and bacon over bread. Cover with grated cheese.
Repeat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour. Dissolve soda in 2 tablespoons water and add soda, lemon juice and nuts.
Beat well and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: "dough" for ornaments or wall hangings
directions: Mix and knead the dough.
Use a rolling pin to flatten the dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Use cookie cutters for shapes or draw and cut your own designs.
Make the eyes, nose and cheeks from rolled up dough.
Moisten the "pieces" to attach to the
base item.
Make a hole for top for hanging with an unsharpened pencil. Air-dry for 48 hours.
Paint or vanish the item and let dry thoroughly.
Attach a piece of yarn or string-tie to hang the ornament.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Chill until almost set, then add remaining ingredients.
Great served in casserole dish or mold.

title: chili rellenos pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with chilies.
Grate cheese on top of chilies.
Beat eggs until fluffy and pour over cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until top is browned.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: asparagus delmonico
directions: Heat cream cheese and milk over low heat.
Stir until smooth. Stir in Blue cheese and onion salt.
Serve over hot asparagus. Top with additional Blue cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine chopped onions, beef, a few dashes of hot sauce and Accent.
Mix with cream cheese.
Form into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together, except use only enough milk to make a muffin consistency.
Add 2 cans of creamed corn. Put 1/2 of the mix in baking pan.
Cook ground beef in small amount of water and drain.
Layer beef, onion, hot peppers, bell pepper and cheese on top of cornmeal mixture.
Add the rest of cornmeal mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, margarine and syrup until fluffy. Add flour. Mix well. Bake in 9 X 13 pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Wipe down sides of pan with wet cloth.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard-crack stage (300°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Stir and pour into buttered pan.
Lift around edges as it cools, stretching candy.
Turn over when firm.
Make it thin. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Mix and place in bottom of oblong cake dish.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, cream cheese, and 1/2 cup salsa in medium saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Spoon approximately 1/2 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place in lightly greased 8 X 12-inch baking dish.

title: unkneaded entire wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Stir molasses and salt into milk and bring to lukewarm, then add yeast mix.
Beat in the flour, enough until the mixture is almost firm enough to knead. Cover and let rise until doubled, cut down and transfer to well-oiled bread pan.
Smooth over top with knife; let stand until almost double.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for about 1 hour.

title: pascal's manale barbecue shrimp
directions: Saute bacon in Dutch oven. In same pan, add all ingredients except shrimp and heat until margarine melts. Add shrimp and stir well. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Serve with sliced French bread for sopping sauce.

title: freezing corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, pack in pint freezer bags or cartons. Freeze.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Serve with bread and assorted vegetables.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute butter and onions until golden brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Pour consomme and water in pan and bring to a boil.
Add onion mixture and reduce heat to low.
Cover soup and simmer for 40 minutes. When serving, add piece of French bread to soup bowl and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake or broil to melt cheese.

title: frosty fruit drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well-greased baking pan. Pour 1 stick melted butter over top.
Bake for 40 minutes in a hot oven at 450°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cut a thin slice off top of each potato.
Scoop out pulp.
Put pulp in bowl.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to pulp.
Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Fill potato skins with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x
13-inch pan 1 stack Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick melted
margarine.
Mix
and place on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Microwave chocolate and butter in bowl on High 1 to 2 minutes until melted, stirring halfway through heating time. Stir in sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell. Bake 50 minutes or until filling is firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt together, using pastry blender. Mix until crumbly.
Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture, stirring to mix.
Form into ball and refrigerate 30 minutes or so.
Roll out on floured surface.

title: cream peach pie
directions: Arrange peach slices in 9-inch pie shell; sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Beat egg and cream together; pour over peaches.
Mix the brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious zucchini puffs
directions: Coarsely grate zucchini.
Should be 2 cups, slightly packed down.
Beat egg until thickened and lemon color.
Add zucchini, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well in large skillet the 2 tablespoons butter.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of zucchini mixture well apart.
When slightly browned, turn puffs and brown on other side.
Add more butter as needed.
Serve hot (yields 14).

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and Milky Way bars in top of double boiler; put aside.
Cream other stick of butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour with soda and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted candy and nuts. Put in 2 or 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Icing using evaporated milk and chocolate chips.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well. Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: make-a-meal-soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine flour with sour cream.
Melt butter and pour into flour and sour cream mixture.
Fold mixture together; will be moist.
Sprinkle flour on mixture to help in rolling into biscuits.
Roll into small balls and place in mini muffin pan. After preheating oven at 425°, bake for approximately 10 minutes. Yields 16 mini biscuits.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in food coloring. Add cereal and stir.
Using buttered fingers, shape 1/4 cup of mixture into wreaths.
Dot with red cinnamon candies.
Yields 16 wreaths.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon and crumble into pieces.
Chop onion.
Shred cheese.
Mix altogether.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Then mix with the first ingredients.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Spread in an ungreased 10 x 14-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Cool.
Then cream the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Then spread over this cherry pie filling.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: steak stew
directions: Cut steak in small pieces.
Dip in flour.
Place in skillet to brown.
Remove steak.
In same oil, cook onions and garlic; mix other seasonings.
Put meat back in skillet; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on box.
Bake and cool. Cut in half, top and bottom.
Cook flour and milk until it thickens and let cool.
Beat sugar, Crisco, oleo, salt and vanilla for 15 minutes.
Add cooled flour mixture and beat 5 more minutes; spread between layers of cake.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with first 5 ingredients; drain fat.
Stir in pizza sauce.
Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
In a large bowl, beat egg and milk.
Add cooked macaroni.
Combine all and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Put Brownie Mix and baking powder in a bowl.
Stir; add water, vanilla and melted shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour topping over batter. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
When cool, turn upside-down on serving dish.
Top with whipped topping or ice cream, if desired.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, evaporated milk, chocolate chips and 1/2 cup butter.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and cool.
Combine cookies and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze until firm.
Sprinkle peanuts over cookie crust.
Spread softened ice cream over peanuts and cover with cooled chocolate mixture.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, bean dip, hot sauce, salt, sour cream, onions and taco seasoning.
Mix, adding one ingredient at a time.
Layer 1/2 of mixture in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle a layer of Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses (mixed) over the top.
Add remaining bean dip mixture on top of cheese, then add the layer of remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: betty crocker golden layer cake
directions: Blend all ingredients for 1/2 minute on low speed and for 3 minutes on high.
Bake in oblong pan for 35 minutes or in layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon butter in a medium mixing bowl; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in milk until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread mixture evenly in bottom of a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover dough with berries; sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Dot with remaining butter.
Pour boiling water over berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash and onion.
Boil until tender; drain thoroughly, then mash.
Add all ingredients, except half of margarine, to squash.
Melt remaining margarine.
Pour mixture into baking dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a small mixing bowl combine onion, bell pepper, squash and eggs; blend well.
Set mixture aside. in another small mixing bowl blend flour, cream, salt and pepper until you have a semi-thick butter.
In a deep casserole dish make a double row of Captain wafer crackers on the bottom.
Next add a 2-inch layer of the squash mixture, then add a 1 inch layer of cheese.
Repeat process until all ingredients are used.
Pour batter on top of casserole and spread butter on top.
Crush remaining wafers and add on top of casserole before baking.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits and water without salt, until mushy.
Mix all ingredients well, except eggs.
Stir in eggs.
Place in greased oblong pan.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 cup fruit juice. Add pineapple and apricots to jello.
Add miniature marshmallows on top of salad.
Mix 1 cup juice, sugar, cornstarch and eggs; cook over medium to low heat until thick.
Let cool and add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of salad and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients.
Combine mixtures and stir until smooth.
Cook on hot greased griddle.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage; rinse and drain.
Add eggs to sausage.
Spread on 15 x 5-inch dough (roll thin).
Sprinkle with ingredients.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Brush top with egg yolk if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown.
Boil cabbage until tender.
Save 2 cups of the liquid from cabbage and drain off excess.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and margarine together and save 1 cup of the mixture for topping.
After saving 1 cup of the mixture, add to remaining egg, milk, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour the mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle over top with the saved topping mixture, crumbled candy bars and chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, simmer sugar and pineapple.
Remove cake from oven; punch holes in cake.
Cover with pineapple.
Cool.

title: beef ala stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Rub meat with garlic, pound flour mixture into meat and cut into tiny pieces.
Melt butter, brown onion and remove.
Put more lard in and brown meat.
Remove meat; add water.
Stir.
Return onion, butter and meat to skillet. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add soup, mushrooms and garlic. Cook uncovered on low heat 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: southern classic waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle orange juice over apples; toss gently and drain. Combine apples, celery and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: john's plum pork chops
directions: Cut a 1-inch piece of trimmed fat from pork chops.
Put in a large skillet.
Brown chops and remove stuffing.
Add onion to drippings in skillet until soft.
Stir in bread crumbs, plums, salt, pumpkin spice and 1/3 cup of lime juice.
Stir lightly.
Put in baking dish pork chops and cover with stuffing.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars in microwave. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crusts. Keep in freezer until time to serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer lettuce, celery, onions and peas.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together; spread on top of peas.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over all.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: evelyn's fudge pie
directions: Melt together baking chocolate and margarine and set aside to cool.
Put remainder of ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat until light.
Add to chocolate mixture and blend well.
Pour fudge mixture into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie becomes firm.
Do not overbake.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine flour, 3/4 c. of the granulated sugar, 1/4 c. of the cocoa powder, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add milk, melted butter and 1/2 t. of the vanilla; stir until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spread batter evenly in baking dish.
In small bowl, whisk together remaining 3/4 c. granulated sugar and 1/4 c. cocoa; gradually stir in boiling water and remaining 1 t. vanilla.
Carefully pour mixture evenly over batter in dish.
Bake 30-35 min. or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 15 min.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Great topped with ice cream and whipped cream.

title: broccoli rabe and pine nuts(italian greens)
directions: Wash and trim thick stems of broccoli rabe and then steam them four about 3 minutes.
Drain broccoli in colander.
Toast the pine nuts.
Set aside the broccoli and nuts.

title: mulligatawny soup(curried cream soup.  serves 6 to 8.)
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and crushed garlic to pot and cook over low heat until onion is soft.
Add flour and curry powder and cook at least two minutes, stirring.
Add half and half and chicken stock and cook over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add apple, peeled and chopped, 10 minutes before serving.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper (just a dash).
Be careful not to bring soup to a boil to avoid curdling. It is the apple which makes the soup so different.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add rice, jar cheese, celery and mushroom soup.
Mix and put into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: unbelievable pie
directions: Blend above in blender for about 3 minutes.
Pour in pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle one cup coconut on top. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange, raisin salad
directions: Mix together in medium bowl.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: peach bisque
directions: In a blender or food processor puree the peaches with the sugar.
Add the sour cream, half and half, cream and half of the spices.
Refrigerate for several hours to draw the flavors.
Stir in the brandy just before serving.
Sprinkle the top of each serving with remaining spices, then top with a dollop of whipped cream or sliced peaches.
If you chill the bowls before filling them, the soup will stay cold longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat the oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan with shortening, using a pastry brush.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and brown.
Use about 2 tablespoons of the bacon grease.
Add pork and beans.
Crumble bacon in beans.
Add brown sugar, cumin, oregano, marjoram, chili powder and hot sauce.
Heat on low flame until well heated.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Combine vegetables; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 4 hours.
