Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: beer barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and brush chicken evenly with about half of it.
Mix remaining butter with barbecue sauce, beer and hot pepper sauce.
Bake chicken, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple and cut in small pieces.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In blender, mix together eggs, butter, sweetener and vanilla.
In large bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Stir in liquid ingredients from blender.
Press in a 12 x 18 x 1-inch cookie pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, checking the bars to make sure they do not burn on bottom.
Let cool and cut into 2 x 3-inch bars.
Serve 12.

title: turkey appetizers
directions: Mix together the first seven ingredients. Cut the chilled cranberry sauce with fluted cookie cutter, slice across the fluted cranberry sauce.
Spread each slice of bread with turkey salad and top each with cranberry star.
Makes about 25 canapes.

title: broccoli japanese chicken
directions: Cook cut up chicken in oil; set aside.
In skillet, add vegetables, water and soy sauce.
Cook until thawed.
Add chicken, ginger and cornstarch.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crusts.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: bananas foster a' la gena
directions: Heat butter in frying pan over medium heat.
When melted, add sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Cook until golden brown.
Add sliced bananas and mix well.
Cook 1 minute.
Add fruit juices; mix and continue cooking 1 minute.
Add flavoring; flambee.
Mix well and serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place split biscuits on top and brown.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Work in just enough flour to roll out dough.
Roll thin; cut with 2-inch cutter.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Do not overbrown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: maxine's green beans
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 350° oven; bake until bubbly.
Serve.

title: cookie dough for cookie press
directions: Place ingredients in bowl and mix.
The dough will be stiff. Place in a cookie press and create.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain and place in greased casserole dish. Saute onion in butter.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz, onion and sour cream.
Pour over broccoli. Top with cheese and bread crumbs, dotted with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: In a 9-inch skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot oil, cook garlic and onion until tender, then add next 5 ingredients. Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil, strawberries and water, then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: turkey zucchini casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/4 stick.
Set pan aside.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Drain
juice
from pineapple and mixed fruit.
Mix with pudding
and cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool and pour over fruit.

title: carrot relish
directions: In
a
medium saucepan, cook the carrots, covered, in a small amount
of	water for 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain. Return
carrots to pan.
Add green peppers, pimientos, vinegar, honey and onions.
Combine sugar, flour, dry mustard, celery
salt and
salt.
Stir into vegetables.	Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.	Cook and stir 3 minutes more. Remove from heat and serve warm or chilled.	Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: baked corn en casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy doughnuts
directions: Take the biscuits with your fingers and pull a hole in the middle. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Remove and drain. Roll in xxx sugar and enjoy!

title: waffles
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Preheat waffle iron.
Spray with nonstick spray.
Use 1/2 cup batter for a 7-inch round or square waffle. Cook waffle for 2 minutes.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: deep dish bubble pizza
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters to put in large mixing bowl.
Mix in spaghetti sauce and garlic.
Add 2 cups cheese and mix well, coating biscuits.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cocoa peanut logs
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir constantly until well blended.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat half the sugar with shortening and butter.
Gradually add milk.
Continue beating. Add extract and gradually add remaining sugar until the right consistency is reached.
Will frost 24 cupcakes.

title: middle east-borek
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Crumble the Feta cheese into a mixing bowl. Add the pepper and nutmeg.
Wash the mint and cut up with scissors. Add to the cheese and mash with a fork until creamy.
Take out the pieces of filo pastry and separate carefully.
Cut them into strips, about 3-inches wide.
Brush strips with oil and put a teaspoonful of Feta in the corner of each one.
Fold as here.
Keep folding so that you end up with fat, little triangles.
Brush with oil and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: maple fizzer(serves 6)
directions: Add maple syrup to milk and mix well.
Divide among 6 tall glasses. Fill with ginger ale.
Serve cold.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt butter
and
marshmallows.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans, raisins
and cherries.
Pack into a 9 x 5-inch pan and
store	in
refrigerator.
Slice
thinly.
Tastes like candy! Is so good!
And I don't care for regular fruit cake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together really well.
Roll into small balls and bake 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy pineapple cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
While cake is baking, mix pudding and refrigerate.
When cake is done but still slightly warm, spread thickened pudding on top.
Add drained crushed pineapple and, when ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Fry and break up ground beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions. When meat is ready, spread evenly over beans. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top of meat.
Put tomatoes and onions on top. Add salsa and spread on sour cream. Add rest of cheese. Serve with taco chips.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients gently for 3 minutes; cool.
Mash the bananas in a blender with the pineapple juice.
Combine the orange juice, lemonade and lemon juice.
Add juices to sugar water mixture; freeze. Spoon frozen mixture into glasses and add 7-Up or place in punch bowl and pour pop over it.
Doubles nicely.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and put into casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and water in pan. Reserve 1/2 liquid. Add rice and mushrooms. Put in baking dish. Lay chicken breast on top and pour reserved soup mix on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour covered. Then bake 15 minutes uncovered.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda and pudding.
Mix well; add chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375°
for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: quick chili
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and onion.
Add to browned seasoned hamburger.
Add canned chili, tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Add chili powder to taste.
Simmer until serving time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab meat canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut into eighths.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with hazelnuts and thyme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place hazelnuts on cookie sheet and toast until brown, about 15 minutes.
Wrap warm hazelnuts in dish towel and rub together to loosen skins.
Unwrap and cool.
Finely chop.
(Can be prepared 4 days ahead.
Store in airtight container.)

title: golden tassies
directions: Let first two ingredients warm to room temperature.
Blend together, then add flour, 1/4 at a time, work in with fingers and chill.
Break off small chunks.
Mold into small sized muffin tins, as for tarts.
Fill with jelly or jam and bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add buttermilk, sugar, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Mix.
Add remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer
vegetables in order given in buttered baking pan or dish.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled northern fish
directions: Fillet fish and cut into small pieces.
Place in jar.
Add 1/2 cup salt for each quart of fish.
Cover with white cider vinegar. Let stand 5 days in refrigerator, then remove and rinse with cold water.
Place fish back in jar and add sliced onions, 1 quart of white vinegar, sugar and pickling spices.
Let stand 1 week.
The longer they stand, the firmer they get.
Enjoy.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Cut cauliflower in small pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp and break into small bits.
Cut up green onions (tops too).
Mix all ingredients with salad dressing or favorite dressing.

title: apricot mousse
directions: Line a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Drain apricots; save 1/2 cup juice. Save 4 halves for garnish.
Puree apricots.
Add gelatin to apricot juice.
Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup of sugar and salt in saucepan; slowly add milk, cooking over medium heat for about 4 minutes, until mixture thickens and reaches 160°.
Add gelatin mixture and cook until dissolved.
Stir in pureed apricots, brandy and sliced almonds.
Chill until thickness of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat whipping cream and 1/2 cup of sugar to soft peaks.
Blend whipped cream into apricot mixture and spoon into spring-form pan.
Garnish with additional whipped cream and apricot halves.
This is very light, airy and delicious.

title: banana-peanut salad
directions: Cut bananas in half and slice long ways to make 4 banana slices per banana.
Thin mayonnaise down with orange juice.
Thin enough so banana will coat when dipped in.
After dipping banana, drain in hand strainer.
Lay coated banana on lettuce and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower about 2 minutes and take out of water, save about 1 cup of water it was cooked in.
In bottom of pan add flour and butter.
Let brown just a little.
Add warm water that cauliflower was cooked in.
Add salt and nutmeg; drop cauliflower back in and steam until tender, about 1 minute.

title: oklahoma baked beans(serves 10 to 15)
directions: Mix together the ingredients and pour into an ovenproof casserole. Bake at 300° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chewy chews(great for kids)
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat. Gradually add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Refrigerate and wait until they harden to chew.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown breasts in hot oil briefly.
Drain oil.
Top breasts with salsa (12 to 16 ounce jar or more, according to number of breasts).
Cook, covered; simmer 30 minutes.
Transfer to serving plate, careful to keep salsa on top.
Top with broken up tortilla chips, then sprinkle with Monterey Jack, the more the merrier. Place in microwave to melt cheese.
Serve over rice.
Yummy!

title: sweet-n-spicy pecans
directions: Melt margarine in microwave dish. Add water, sugar and spices. Mix to make syrup. Add pecans. Stir to coat. Cook on high for 2 minutes, stir. Cook on high for 2 minutes, stir. Cook on high for 60 to 90 seconds more. Cool on waxed paper.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic.
Stir in beef and cook until brown.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil the margarine and water; stir until smooth.
Add sugar, flour and Nestle Quick.
Add buttermilk and soda; stir until smooth, then add eggs and vanilla.
Stir well; pour into greased pan.
Spread icing on cake while hot.

title: bean dish
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and break in small pieces.
Add ground beef and onions and cook until beef is brown and onions are soft.
Add all ingredients to slow cooker and cook 4 to 5 hours on low.

title: economy mincemeat
directions: Cook hamburger, water and salt until done. Combine rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 40 minutes.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in skillet.
Add broth and soup, mix well.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and soy sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Stir in rice.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Sprinkle cashews and noodles over top.
Bake until brown (about 12 minutes).
Yields 8 servings.

title: dilled macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and carrot; toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients; gently stir mayonnaise mixture into macaroni mixture. Chill 1 hour.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil in bowl. Add cold water. If dough seems dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of oil, not water. Roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Makes 1 (10-inch) crust.

title: vanilla butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings by hand.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs in melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla and stick of butter for 10 minutes (important step).
Add eggs and continue to beat.
Spread over crumb layer.
Peel bananas and slice over cream layer.
Drain pineapple thoroughly.
Spoon over banana.
Cover with Cool Whip. Chill 4 hours or more.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cover apricots with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and cut up.
Blend next 3 ingredients as for pie crust (cut in butter) and pack into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: For pie, use 1 3/4 cups milk.
Pour into pie shell.

title: pumpkin pie or squash or cushaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust. Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, then reduce oven to 275° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Add frozen vegetables when noodles are half cooked.
Continue cooking until noodles are done. Drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup and chicken.
Cook until hot.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over pasta.

title: kolache
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar; let stand.
Scald milk in saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add salt and egg yolks.
Combine milk mixture and yeast in large bowl. Bit by bit, add the flour and mix.
Leave some flour to put on board.
Knead dough until glossy.
Place in bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled.
Now, using a tablespoon, take egg-sized bits of dough and roll into balls.
Place on greased baking sheet, 1 inch apart.
Brush with butter; let rise until light.
Make an indentation in each, large enough to hold 1 teaspoonful of fruit filling.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Core and finely chop apples.
Put apples and cider in microwave-safe bowl. Cover tightly.
Microwave on High 15 minutes. Remove cover. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Microwave on High 10 minutes, uncovered. Stir every 2 to 3 minutes.
Process in blender until smooth. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put cooked broccoli in baking dish, place chicken on top. Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice and curry together.
Pour over the broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix everything together except fruit.
Drain oranges and then mix.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer for 30 seconds.
Use cornstarch and water to thicken mixture.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Stir together the first seven ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to salad before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine; add broccoli with water.
Stir and simmer.
Add soup and cheese. Simmer again.
Add rice and stir. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fat-free pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to box. Chop green onions, greens and all.
Chop tomatoes.
Mix green onions, tomatoes, Salad Supreme and fat-free Italian dressing together.
Stir in cooked macaroni. Refrigerate. Stays nice for a few days.
Quick and easy.

title: zippy pork and beans
directions: Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and heated through.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Place broken pieces of meat in frying pan.
Add onion and green pepper; fry until meat is well browned.

title: chocolate salami
directions: In a large bowl beat the egg yolks and the sugar, when it's creamy add the cookies crumbled in large pieces, rum and melted butter, cocoa and then almonds.
Mold the mixture into the shape of a salami, then roll it on confectioners sugar and wrap it with aluminum foil, put in the fridge for a few hours then slice it and serve.

title: sweet-sour ham and rice skillet
directions: Cook ham and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Add water to pineapple juice as needed to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid and rest of ingredients to ham mixture.
Stir to blend. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and cook until liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill. Spread mixture on bread.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Mix
flour, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar, margarine and pecans and
pat
this
mixture
into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until slightly browned.
Cool.

title: hamburger ring barbecue
directions: Blend all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Pack firmly into a 9-inch ring mold or bundt pan.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn ring out onto a jelly roll pan or other cookie sheet.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat (use at least half bottle) and continue cooking at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: kolacky(christmas cookie)
directions: Mix.
Roll in balls.
Press for thumb print.
Fill with solo fruit filling.
Bake 400° for 20 minutes.
Check at 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot pasta
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to spaghetti sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer; cook shells.
Layer in a crock-pot as follows: sauce, shells, more sauce, cheese.
Repeat these layers until all ingredients are added, ending with grated cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: wile e's flank steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, wine, garlic and ginger powder.
Score flank steak on both sides.
Marinate steak in mixture for about 6 hours (or overnight).
Broil on grill until well done.
Serves 4.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain juice from all vegetables.
Heat sugar and vinegar to dissolve; add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate for several hours before serving. This will keep for several weeks in refrigerator in a tightly covered bowl.
Yields 3 pints.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Flatten out a biscuit. Spread with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
You can also top with your other favorite toppings.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes (until biscuit is done).

title: chicken liver casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in fat and remove from pan.
Roll livers in flour and brown.
Slice squash and parboil for 5 minutes.
Mix together catsup and water; set aside.
Alternate livers, squash, mushrooms and onion; cover with catsup and water mixture and seasonings.
Cover and bake in one-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma anderson's jello
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water with Jell-O.
Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to make 1 cup.
Add to jello and refrigerate until slightly thick.
Whip jello; add crushed pineapple.
Whip cream and cream cheese; fold all ingredients into jello.
Pour into a greased jello mold.
Chill until firm.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Pour applesauce in a baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over applesauce.
Mix brown sugar and pecans.
Sprinkle over cake mix. Slice butter over top and cover top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift together powdered sugar and flour.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon salt on medium until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until peaks form.
Fold in gradually flour mixture.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake on lowest rack in a 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cover with cheese bits and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and bow ties
directions: Cook broccoli for 3 minutes in large pot of boiling salted water. Remove the broccoli from water with a slotted spoon or sieve. Place in a large bowl and set aside.

title: picante cornbread
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Add milk, egg and oil, mixing well.
Add meat, onion, pepper, picante sauce and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: shoo-fly crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, both sugars, salt and butter until crumbly, using a pastry blender.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for the topping. Mix molasses, boiling water and the baking soda.
Gradually add this "witches brew" to the dry ingredients until well blended (like cake batter).
Pour the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the reserved cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes bake
directions: Place potatoes and enough water to cover in a large pan; cover and cook for 25 to 35 minutes or just tender.
Drain; cool slightly and peel.
In large bowl, mash potatoes; stir in butter, sugar and raisins.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with nuts and marshmallows.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: souper meat and potato pie
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings thoroughly.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	until tender;
drain and layer a casserole dish
with	broccoli.
Then
place	cheese	slices	over broccoli. Spread
cracker
crumbs over cheese.
Slice 1 stick of butter over crackers and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: canuck stew
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces.
Fry until most of the grease is extracted.
Remove bacon and put flour in the fat.
Blend smooth, then add water slowly.
Stir and cook until flour thickens, then add dried beef, potatoes and onions.
Cover skillet and cook 20 minutes.
Thin with a little hot water if too thick.
Serves 4.

title: raisin date cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla; gradually add the dry ingredients.
Stir in the raisins, oats, nuts and dates.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onion.
Season while cooking with salt and pepper.
Add soups and enchilada sauce.
Pour into casserole dish or long flat cake pan.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Eat with tortilla chips as spoons.

title: honey bran muffins
directions: Combine 100% Bran Buds and water; let cool.
In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and honey.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in buttermilk and Brand Buds mixture.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt; stir into bran mixture.
Fold in All-Bran cereal.
Heat oven to 375°; fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Batter can be stored in tightly covered container in refrigerator up to 30 days.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown onions and chops in skillet.
While that is being done, cook rice until done.
Drain and put a layer of onions and chops in baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over each layer and on top. Bake at 350° until chops are done.
Serve on rice.

title: spanish cream
directions: Soak gelatin in cold milk for 10 minutes; add sugar and salt and stir
until
it
is dissolved.	Heat in top of double boiler until milk is scalded.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add 1/2 cup hot
milk.	Stir mixture into remaining milk and cook until slightly thickened (about 4 minutes).
Stir constantly. Remove from
heat	and
cool slightly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Turn into molds and chill until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water. Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a deep baking dish.
Place sliced apples and water in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls onto cookie sheet.
Prepare rolls as per package instructions (brown lightly and cool).
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise and spread on dough.
Chop up vegetables and add to crust.

title: tex mex
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium size bowl.
In separate bowl, add lemon juice, salt and pepper, sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip over plate first, then spread avocados.
Then spread other mixture over this.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover it all with Cheddar cheese.

title: salisbury steak dinner
directions: Combine beef, 1/4 cup onion soup, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well and shape into oblong patties.
Brush skillet with oil.
Dip patties into flour.
Brown both sides over medium heat.
Pour off fat and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining soup, 1/2 cup water, 1 tablespoon ketchup and 1 tablespoon sugar in small bowl.
Pour into skillet and stir to loosen brown bits.
Pour over patties.
Cover with foil and bake 25 minutes.
Turn patties.
Bake 20 more minutes.

title: chicken with white spaghetti sauce
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save the broth to cook pasta.
In a large saucepan, slowly melt cream cheese in milk.
Use a whisk to smooth out sauce.
Add green onions and seasoning.
Let cook for 15 minutes.
Add deboned chicken and cook for another 15 minutes. Take off fire and let cool a little.
Sauce will thicken.
Cook pasta in chicken broth and strain.
Pour sauce over pasta and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and place in bowl.
Prepare pudding according to instructions and add to Cool Whip.
Add to fruit and stir; mix well.

title: butterscotch brickle bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and brown sugar until crumbly. Press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate black walnut cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, eggs, black walnut flavoring and sugar; set aside.
Sift together salt, baking powder, cocoa and flour.
Add to mixture alternately the dry ingredients and the milk.
Add walnuts last.
Bake in large greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°. Take out of oven and cool 10 minutes, then put in cake tin and cover.
Ice later when cool.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Work in fat with a fork or knife.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly, then add enough liquid to make a soft dough.
Roll the dough lightly to about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into biscuits and bake 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: russian tea 1
directions: Mix and store in jar or tightly sealed tin.

title: luau cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add other ingredients. Stir with spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into tube pan, greased and floured.
Cook at 325° approximately 1 hour and 25 minutes or until tests done.

title: daddy's slop #7
directions: Brown hamburger (crumble) and chopped onion.
Drain grease. Add corn, chopped tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Cook until hot.

title: krazy kake
directions: (1) Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.

title: auburn eggs delight
directions: Remove crust from bread; cube and place in bottom of greased baking dish (about 11 x 14-inch).
Melt cheese and oleo together and pour over bread cubes.
Layer ham and parsley over cheese. Beat eggs well with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread, cheese and ham mixture.
Do not stir.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
Good with Danish or coffee cake and fresh fruit.

title: quick chicken parmigiana
directions: In 2 qt shallow baking dish arrange patties. Top each with 1/4 cup pasta sauce. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until chicken is hot and cheese is melted. Heat remaining sauce until hot. Serve sauce with chicken and spaghetti.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix and shape in patties (should make approximately 12 patties).
Refrigerate until ready to cook.
Fry the patties over medium heat, 4 to 5 at a time, for about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on each side, or until golden brown in oil.
(Use vegetable, peanut or corn oil.)

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: speed bake cinnamon rolls
directions: In the morning cream together the shortening, sugar and salt. Add beaten egg.
Sift and measure flour into a mixing bowl.
Blend in yeast ferment.
Then add creamed mixture; knead into a smooth dough, not too stiff.
Let rise until doubled, if desired.
Knead down and let rise again until doubled.
Shape into a roll.
Let rise in an oiled tin until doubled.

title: yoda's incredible stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; add all ingredients and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Use fresh spinach that is well rinsed and tough stems have been removed.
Simmer spinach for 5 minutes and add to stew.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Use very ripe bananas for best results, about 2 medium.

title: 3 day yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Boil 1 cup water; add margarine to melt.
Cool slightly.
In large bowl of heavy-duty mixer, put cool water and the eggs, mixing well.
Add warm water and margarine mix, then dissolved yeast and sugar, mixing well. Measure flour and salt; slowly add flour to liquid mixture, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
(You can use heavy-duty mixer with dough hook.) After mixing thoroughly, place dough in a greased large bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: friendship salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add juices from orange and pineapple and enough water to make 2 cups and add to jello.
Add pineapple and chill.
Arrange orange slices on top of jello; add marshmallows.
Combine whipped cream and mayonnaise; spread over top of salad.
Grate cheese over top and chill for 24 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift dry ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
Put eggs, butter, buttermilk, lemon and sugar in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add nuts and chop.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix only until flour is moist.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, grease a loaf pan.
Mix cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in orange juice, egg and carefully fold in cranberry mixture.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spoon over the chicken. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all, set
dish
in
a pan of water in 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup and 1/2 of the onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Peel, quarter and cook potatoes until tender and golden brown. Sprinkle with butter and paprika.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 smaller ones.
Dot with butter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruity macaroons
directions: Beat
together the margarine, salt, sugar and egg.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes at 350°.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Add milk and oil, stirring until dough clings together.
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead 7 to 8 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and bake on ungreased pan at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 18 biscuits.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, vanilla, milk, soda and baking powder. Gradually add flour. Drop by tablespoon on sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced party nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix spices in a bowl; set aside.
Heat the oil in a nonstick skillet over low heat.
Add the spice mixture, stirring well.
Add the nuts and stir well to coat thoroughly, 3 to 4 minutes.
Spread nuts on a cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes, tossing once.

title: garlic chicken bites
directions: Marinate chicken strips in olive oil, garlic and pepper for 30 minutes.
Drain off excess marinade.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix bread crumbs with cayenne.
Dip both sides of chicken strips in mixture.
Arrange strips in one layer on a baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn and bake 5 minutes more until browned.

title: chili con queso(microwave)
directions: Cube Velveeta and melt in microwave, stirring frequently. Drain and chop pimientos, chilies and tomatoes.
Fold into cheese. Keep warm; great with tortilla chips and as a topping for baked potatoes.

title: king's ransom casserole
directions: Prepare mostaccioli according to package directions.
Drain. In large skillet, combine ground beef, onion and celery.
Cook until beef is browned and celery is tender, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and spaghetti sauce mix to browned ground beef.
Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Layer ingredients in a 3-quart baking dish: mostaccioli, sauce and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll in small balls and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: aunt hattie's hermits
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in egg until fluffy.
Add milk gradually with dry ingredients that have been mixed together. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in moderate oven or until done and lightly browned.

title: mix-easy 2 egg cake
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into sifter. Measure shortening into bowl.
Measure milk and vanilla into cup. Mix or stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add 1/2 of liquid and the eggs.
Mix until all flour is dampened, then beat 1 minute.
Add remaining liquid.
Blend and beat 2 minutes longer.
Frost as desired.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, flour and cocoa. Combine muffin mix with milk and add to sugar mixture; beat well. Add vanilla and melted margarine. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in order as given.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together; add 1/4 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch greased pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Good topped with Cool Whip when served.

title: mexican cheese casserole
directions: Place
chicken	in
casserole
dish.
Sprinkle	chopped onion over
it, then sprinkle grated cheese next. Crush chips and sprinkle
half of the bag over the cheese.	Mix soups and Ro-Tel (do
not
add
water to the soup) in mixing bowl. Pour this mixture
over
the	casserole.
Sprinkle the rest of the chips
on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: broccoli orange salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and add dressing just before serving.

title: zesty fat-free appetizer
directions: Spread rolls out on cookie sheet and cook according to directions on package.
Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 9-inch square casserole dish.
Put a layer of cheese.
Add the rest of the mixture and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well by hand and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from side of pan.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly; cut into bars.

title: ham crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough to 4 long rectangles. Press perforations to seal.
Place ham on each rectangle. Spread with mustard; sprinkle with cheese.
Start with short end and roll up; press to seal.
Coat with sesame seed.
Cut each of 4 rolls into 5 slices forming 20 slices in all.
Place cut side down on ungreased side on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or golden brown.
Remove from sheet and serve warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 cookie sheets.
Keep warm.
Mix baking soda, water and vanilla.
Mix sugar, 1 cup water and syrup in 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally to 240° or forms soft ball in cold water.
Stir in oleo and peanuts.
Cook, stirring always, to 300° or in brittle threads.
Don't let it burn.
Quickly add baking soda to mixture until light and foamy.
Pour candy onto cookie sheets.
Cool and break into pieces.
Makes about 6 dozen candies.

title: impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Put all together and blend for 15 seconds.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and drain grease; add onions, sauce, soup and olives, cook about 10 minutes.
Fry tortillas in oil until soft. Layer cake pan with tortillas, layer of meat mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat until gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Boil sugar and water together for about 3 minutes; let cool. Add juice of 3 lemons and 3 oranges, crushed pineapple and mashed bananas.
Mix and freeze in popsicle holders.

title: cheese taters
directions: Prepare potatoes according to instructions on package.
Add cream cheese, egg and onion.
Whip potatoes and other ingredients until blended together.
Pour into greased 11 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes, or until top is lightly golden.

title: haydee's nacho dip
directions: Cook ground beef; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Cut cheese into small pieces in bowl; add milk and melt in microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.
Get a glass baking dish.
Layer the beans, then ground beef and then cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes until scum forms and browns.
Stir and bake 10 or 15 minutes longer until scum forms again.
Stir in sugar and raisins; bake until bubbles (boils) in center.

title: meat marinade
directions: Put meat in large bag.
Pour in marinade and tie off.
Rotate every four hours, letting it marinate overnight.
Excellent on London broil, flank steak and pot roasts.
Excellent tenderizer.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O. Stir until dissolved in large bowl. Add sugar and crushed pineapple. Freeze until it begins to thicken.

title: skillet chicken divan
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until brown.
Add water, veggies, soup and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Serve.
Use a large skillet or wok.

title: tuna melt burgers
directions: Flake tuna into a bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well; split bun and butter both sides.
Fill with tuna mixture; put sandwich in a piece of foil, wrap sealing tightly each sandwich; place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and bananas; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients then add alternately with milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch sheet pan or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet relish (or chow chow)
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and squeeze.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil mixture 5 minutes.
Can in hot cans.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until tender (approximately 1/2 hour).
Drain and cool.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Crumble crackers.
Layer crackers and oysters in casserole dish.
Combine milk, butter and onion in saucepan; add juice from oysters.
Cook until onion becomes translucent.
Pour mixture over crackers and oysters.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fredda ann taylor's hot punch
directions: Stud each slice of orange with 4 whole cloves.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and cook slowly all day.

title: apple downside-up cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat butter in a round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch, in oven, until melted.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Arrange apples on sugar mixture in pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat and garlic.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles. Heat oven to 350°.
Alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles and cut cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, beginning and ending with meat sauce.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: valentine punch
directions: The morning before using, fill ice cube tray with water and put a maraschino cherry in each ice cube compartment; freeze.
At time to use, mix frozen juice concentrate with 4 cups water and maraschino cherry juice in glass pitcher.
Add maraschino ice cubes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in shortening until transparent.
Add drained tomatoes and spices.
Stir in cheese and continue to cook over low heat until mixture is well blended.
This dip must be served quite hot.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: open face pizza burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place on English muffins or hamburger buns.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well mixed.
Makes about 16 pancakes.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk, vegetable oil and egg together.
Add mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach bacon salad
directions: Make dressing by combining olive oil; vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Wash, drain and dry spinach.
Tear into bite size pieces and place in salad bowl.
Halve avocado, remove pit, skin and slice thin.
Place in small bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Add minced onion and 2 teaspoons of dressing and toss lightly.
Pour dressing over spinach and toss lightly again.
Add avocado and toss.
Cook bacon in 1 teaspoon olive oil; when crisp and brown, pour over spinach mixture, fat and all.
Break up bacon pieces and add to mixture and toss.
Top with croutons and serve all at once.

title: harvest minestrone
directions: Fry bacon; drain and chop.
In bacon fat, saute for 5 minutes the next 6 ingredients.
Add the following 5 ingredients and saute for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and beef bouillon mixture.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients with reserved bacon.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: skillet pork chop casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook the pork chops.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on the box.
Add cream of chicken soup and stir well.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and cook until Rice-A-Roni is done.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add tomato soup, pecans, olives, mayonnaise, celery, and cream cheese.
Mix.
Fold in shrimp and onion, if desired.	Pour mixture into 9 inch x 12 inch glass dish. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: angel flake yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix yeast mixture with buttermilk, sugar and salt; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda together.
Cut in shortening.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Do not knead.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pinch off amount needed.
Knead, roll, cut and bake.
Don't allow to rise.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill. (Pour some of this into a mold to form an ice ring.)
Pour over ice in a punch bowl.
Add chilled ginger ale.
Serve at once. Makes 50 half-cup servings.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring occasionally and watch it doesn't burn. Blend in the chocolate chips, flour, graham cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Spread in well-buttered 12 x 8-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: open house punch
directions: Dump all of the ingredients into a large bowl (do not add water).
Stir and serve.

title: strawberry parfait
directions: Blend all together, pour into tall, chilled glasses and top with scoop of vanilla or strawberry ice cream.

title: huckleberry cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with creamed mixture, milk, syrup and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Coat berries with additional flour and gently fold in.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 9 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan or angel food pan. In a large bowl, cream together 1/2 cup butter and the sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, beating well.
Mix in the 2 cups flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sour cream and vanilla, blending well.
In a separate bowl, combine the nuts, brown sugar, 3 tablespoons of flour, 3 tablespoons butter and cinnamon.
Mix together to form a crumb topping.
Spread half of the batter into prepared pan and sprinkle with half the topping.
Cover with remaining batter and topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add pecans and butter; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to soft boil.
Remove from heat and stir with a wooden spoon for 2 to 3 minutes until it thickens.
Drip by rounded tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: mom's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Throw away those boxes with the fluorescent orange powdered cheese.
This is the real thing.

title: oven corn bread
directions: Beat egg.
Stir dry ingredients together, then combine with liquids.
Stir until smooth.
Cook at 425° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frosty supreme jello salad
directions: Add vinegar, onion salt, sour cream and mayonnaise to jello. Let cool until syrupy.
Add cucumber that has been drained.
Put in a mold and refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add onion to broccoli; cook and drain.
Melt margarine; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk; cook until thickened. Add remaining ingredients.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and onion and simmer.
Press biscuits into greased muffin pans (make sure dough is up to top of cup).
Fill with meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Makes 20 cups.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg whites at high speed in electric mixer (2 minutes).
Reduce speed to low and beat for 1 minute.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and slowly pour cream of coconut over cake while still warm.
Let cool. Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with remaining coconut or as much as you like.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: twice baked squash
directions: Halve and clean squash.
Cook until tender.
Remove pulp and mix with all ingredients.
Fill squash shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Heat first three ingredients in oven and saute.
Mix cooked beans and soup with first mixture.
Top with American or Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Place in large bowl the chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and butter.
Bring to boil the butter, sugar and evaporated milk. Turn to low, stirring 9 minutes. Pour on chocolate chips. Mix until melted. Pour into buttered pan and chill.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt. Beat egg white and cold water to a froth. Add pecans and cover well. Add egg coated pecans to cinnamon sugar. Spread on a buttered cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and pack in closed cans.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Mix sugar and eggs.
Add to butter and cocoa.
Add flour, vanilla, and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a well greased pan.
Bake at 300 for 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes until thick, stirring all the while.
Add vanilla.
Fill pie shell and cover with beaten egg whites.
Place in moderate oven until meringue is brown.

title: munchy onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Soak in ice water for 2 hours.
Drain onions dry.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Dip onions in batter.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in top of a double boiler. Add flakes with a rubber spatula. Leave over hot water until you have dropped all cookies out with a spoon. Refrigerate until set. Then you can store them at room temperature.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Soak
bread
in
milk.
Mix meat, egg and soaked bread. Make balls and fry in cooking oil until done.

title: baked (mock fried) chicken
directions: Wash chicken. Drain on paper towels. Dip into oil, then onto crumbled crackers. Salt lightly, pepper, turn over and coat other side with crackers. Place on baking sheet. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test with fork for tenderness.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, nuts and coconut.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large or 6 small loaves.
Spray pans with Pam.

title: high calcium cabbage bread(high calcium, low calorie)
directions: Place cabbage in a small bowl and toss with lemon juice; set aside.
Combine yogurt, orange juice, sugar, oil, powdered milk and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in cabbage.
In a large bowl, combine flours, sesame seed, baking powder, soda, salt, mace and ginger; mix well.
Gradually add cabbage mixture to flour mixture; mix until they are combined.
Pour batter in a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with soup or salad meal.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients together.
Shape the mixture into balls and brown them in a pan with the oleo.
While the balls are browning, slice the onion and add it and the mushrooms to the pan.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Add the beef broth and 2 tablespoons sherry.
Mix the flour with 1/4 cup water.
Add to the liquid in the pan.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes. Serves 5 people.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Pound chicken and place in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine spinach, mushrooms, onion, Ricotta cheese and pepper in bowl. Spoon some spinach mixture into each chicken and roll. Save some mixture and spoon over chicken. Combine gravy and thyme and spoon over chicken. Cover and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. About 10 minutes before chicken is done, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
but 1/2 can soup and 1/2 onion; put in baking
dish.
Mix
cup water and 1/3 cup catsup. Pour over meat
loaf.
Bake
3/4 to 1 hour at 375°.
Cook 1/2 can soup, 1/2 can water and 1/2 onion for sauce.

title: cream cheese dessert roll
directions: Have the cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and instant pudding by hand.
Blend or fold in fruit cocktail. Shape into a roll or ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with graham crackers.
Serves 26.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Pour peaches with syrup into ungreased rectangular pan. Top with dry cake mix. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with coconut and pecans. Bake for 60 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix well the cake mix and egg.	Fold in Cool Whip.
Make small ball; roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Be sure to use Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Great with any fresh vegetables.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg and enough milk to make thin batter.
Pour into hot, well-greased pan.
Bake until brown in hot oven.

title: sweet potato rings
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with sugar, butter and cream (milk).
Put in a baking dish, making a ring around the edge of dish, leaving center for sauce.

title: french toast
directions: Break egg into bowl.
Mix milk, sugar, salt and vanilla with the egg.
Beat this mixture until egg yolk is blended with white, but not frothy.
Place frying pan on medium heat.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to melt and cover bottom of pan.
Dip pieces of bread into egg mixture.
Place into skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.
Serve with jam, jelly or syrup.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Brown hamburg, onion and salt in skillet.
Combine mushroom soup and milk and pour over hamburger.
Add to noodles and place in a buttered baking dish and place bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: dressing for banana salad
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 2 sticks of butter.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shirl's hamburg deluxe
directions: Saute Spanish onions sliced into frying pan.
When brown, add diced tomatoes; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add hamburg patties in 1/4 pound patties (nice and fat).
Cook for 1 1/2 hours (keep turning). Pour gravy over mashed potatoes and enjoy.

title: lebanese salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bottle with top.
Shake each time you use it.
Makes enough to serve a family of 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together; beat until creamy and smooth.
Put in ready-made graham cracker crust.
Top with 1 can pie cherries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: date balls
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and chopped dates until thick.
Remove from heat. Add nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring.
Cool.
Make into balls and lightly roll in powdered sugar.
These keep nicely in a covered container.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add hamburger and onions.
Cook slowly.
Add peppers and garlic.
Simmer.
Add
spaghetti sauce, oregano and salt. Put drained zucchini in casserole.
Pour sauce over.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry whipped pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water 3 minutes. Cool with ice. Remove any unmelted ice. Blend in Cool Whip until smooth. Fold in fruit.
Chill if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into graham cracker crust. Chill 2 hours.

title: mystery  pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese,

1 egg, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla and salt at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with pecans. Mix together corn syrup, remainder of eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour mixture over pecans. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.

title: old timey banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Spread a small amount of custard over bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover with wafers.
Top with layer of sliced bananas.
Add more custard and wafers.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Don't beat egg whites until they become dry and tough.
Put on top of pudding and spread to cover entire surface, sealing well the edges.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate for 48 hours.

title: christmas eve punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, pineapple juice, orange juice, sugar, lemon juice and almond extract.
To serve, add ginger ale, stirring well.

title: peanut stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Cut around edge of each half, leaving a half-inch rim.
Remove pulp, chop and set aside. Heat oil in very large skillet.
Put shells in skillet.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes on each side, coating well with oil.
Remove shells; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Add eggplant pulp, tomato, thyme, red pepper and salt.
Cook, stirring, for 10 minutes, or until eggplant is soft.
Stir in peanuts and crumbs.
Arrange eggplant shells in shallow baking dish.
Fill with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Serve on cooked rice, if desired.

title: appetizer spinach balls
directions: Defrost, drain and squeeze spinach dry.
Mix with everything else. Chill about 2 hours.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
If freezing, freeze on cookie sheet then store in plastic bags.
Thaw before baking at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with mustard cream sauce for dipping.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs and cinnamon in bowl. Mix well.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 24 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening, salt and spices.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Add molasses and blend.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda; add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add boiling water and beat until smooth. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean from center.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: salami
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Re-mix and refrigerate 24 more hours.
Shape in 5 (2-inch) balls. Bake in shallow pan at 150° for 5 hours.
Turn after 3 hours.

title: appetizer cocktail pizza rounds
directions: Spread meat on rye, then put 1 teaspoon spaghetti sauce with mushrooms on meat, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease either a bundt pan, 2 loaf pans, or (2) 9-inch round pans. Measure and beat sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well. Stir in bananas. Alternately adding dry ingredients with milk. Beat 3 minutes. Bake layers 35 to 45 minutes, bake bundt pan for 45 minutes.

title: punch for 50
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in the boiling water. Add remaining ingredients except the ginger ale.
Mix well. Freeze in plastic jugs.
Remove 1 hour before serving.
At time of serving, add ginger ale to taste.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cover the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with slices of bread.
Mix eggs, salt, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with cheese and ham.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine until tender.
Add to cornbread and stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: white bread(ms. tress hoernig's hot rolls and bread)
directions: Put salt and lard in flour; work together.
Dissolve yeast in pint of lukewarm water.
Add to mixture and mix bread to form a stiff dough.
Add more warm water as needed to use up all of flour.
Knead about 20 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic like.
Grease top and let rise to twice its size.
Punch down and let it rise again.
Make into loaves or rolls; let rise until double in size again.
Takes about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fix jello as directed on box.
Let set to cool, but not jell. Grind up cranberries and orange in blender.
Add sugar and pecans. Mix with partially congealed jello.
Refrigerate.

title: quick-n-easy meat patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into patties.
Fry in margarine.
Top with cheese.
Makes 6 patties.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook bacon with onions until onions are tender.
Add cabbage. Cook until tender.
Add noodles.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix the
flour,
salt, pepper and paprika together in a bag. Remove skins from chicken breasts and shake in mixture.

title: fluffy lemon fruit pie
directions: Spread 1/2 of the pie filling over bottom of crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer or wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk until well blended.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until smooth.
Gently stir in half of the whipped topping.
Spread over cherry pie filling, then spread remaining 1/2 of cherry pie filling over pudding mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip around edge of cherry pie filling.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes, discarding marinade.
Chop artichokes.
In a medium bowl, combine artichokes, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Turn into a lightly greased, 1-quart baking dish.

title: cranberry appetizer meatballs
directions: In a bowl, mash cranberry sauce with chili sauce and brown sugar; set aside.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours in a covered pan.
(To brown potatoes, remove top of pan the last 10 to 20 minutes.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix in order and roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: garden pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on a cookie sheet to form a "pizza" crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch.

title: mexicali platter
directions: On a large platter, mound in layers, starting with the refried beans and ending with the scallions.
Serve with Doritos chips or similar.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Cover with mayonnaise and chill.
Just before serving, mix in mayonnaise.
You may put the seed of the avocado in the bowl during chilling to keep salad from turning dark.

title: mediterranean green beans(lo-fat)
directions: Steam beans for 5 minutes or until just tender.
In a large bowl, whisk together vinegar, mustard, garlic, oregano and pepper. Add beans and toss to coat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lite chocolate pound cake
directions: Pour into tube pan (sprayed with Pam) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, combine crumbs and margarine; mix well.
Press 1 1/2 cups crumbs firmly on bottom of 9-inch pan.
In mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy. On low speed, add flour; mix well.
Gradually add milk; beat until smooth.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla. Pour 6 cups of batter in prepared pan over crust.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool to room temperature; chill thoroughly before cutting.

title: green chile
directions: Cook roast for about 30 minutes in stew pot on top of stove. Add remainder of ingredients and cook (with 1/2-inch of water on the bottom).
Do this until the roast falls apart.
Shred roast with fork.

title: wassail(holiday punch)
directions: In large pan, heat cider and one cinnamon stick to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover, stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except for the beef.
Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cup beef and simmer an additional 15 minutes.

title: pound cake #1
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream margarine.
Add sugar slowly, beating between additions.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla; blend in dry ingredients gradually, alternating with milk.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread dough but do not let it rise.
Cut into 24 pieces. Dip each piece in melted oleo and place in layers in Bundt pan. Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken a-la-king
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull off bone and add rest of ingredients to broth.
Cook 30 minutes and thicken with the flour.
Serve over biscuits.

title: dominick's baked tomatoes
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and basil in small bowl.
Place tomato slices in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour dressing over tomatoes and sprinkle with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: *These make the magic.

title: meat balls - canton - tease
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad oil. Form into 1-inch balls. Fry in salad oil in large skillet; drain.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, allspice and water.
Boil until thick.
Add salt and lemon.
Have apples packed into jars, pour sugar mixture over apples and seal.
Boil in water for 30 minutes.
Makes 7 cans.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Cook noodles in a large pot with olive oil and oregano. Drain.
Defrost shrimp.
Cook Alfredo sauce according to package directions, adding shrimp to sauce.
Serve over noodles with side salad and garlic bread.
Serves 4.

title: banana dressing
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until almost candy. Grind the peanuts.
Roll the bananas in the dressing, then in the chopped peanuts.

title: chicken bake
directions: Bake in greased shallow cake pan 30 to 35 minutes at 400°. Serve with chicken gravy.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a jar with a lid.
Cover and shake. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Peel and slice 6 large potatoes.
Cover with water, salt, onion and celery.
Cook until most water is gone and add enough milk to make pot half full.
In a small bowl, mix together 1 egg, 1 teaspoon of water and enough flour so this will be crumbly; use fingers.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 stick of butter and serve.

title: orange-walnut muffins
directions: Lightly oil 12 muffin cups and dust with little oat bran. Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine oat bran, walnuts, baking powder and orange peel in large bowl.
Add orange juice and oil.
Mix until combined.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks begin to appear. Stir sugar into egg whites and continue beating until whites form stiff peaks.
Fold into batter and fill muffin cups.
Bake for 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, Crisco and margarine until well blended.
Add ice water, one spoonful at a time.
Chill in the refrigerator for about 10 minutes (it will roll out better).
I cut this recipe in half to make a two-crust pie.
For a single-crust pie, bake at 400° on a cookie sheet.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine or butter for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Combine rice, vegetables and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: 1st Layer:
In glass 9 X 13 pan, spread beans.

title: hot cheese spread
directions: In 9-inch pie plate or dish, place sliced onion.
Combine mayo and cheese and spread over onion.
Top with chopped olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and sour cream and let set overnight.
In a large container, mix fruit and pecans (as many nuts as you would like).
Add cream-Cool Whip mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients, except vanilla and spices.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add vanilla.
Pour into bowl; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° about 25 minutes (onion and celery should be done).
Chill before using.

title: creole style tomatoes and corn
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserve drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: black and white chocolate strawberries
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper in small microwave bowl. Combine the chocolate chips and liqueur.
Hold berry by hull; dip the berry halfway into the chocolate.
Set on wax paper.
In another bowl, melt the white chocolate on high.
Stir once, until melted and smooth, about 1 minute.
Dip fork in the white chocolate.
Drizzle over the strawberry.
Refrigerate until the chocolate hardens.
Serve chilled.
Servings:

title: krispy delight
directions: Melt the almond bark, then stir in peanut butter.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Delicious!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix bananas and eggs together in a large bowl.
Stir in the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add the pecans and blend.
Pour batter into the loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean. Remove the bread from the pan and cool on rack.
Serve warm or cool.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, garlic, oregano and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Shake and set aside.
Remove skin from chicken.
Cover it lightly with a little olive oil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook on the barbecue.
Place cooked chicken on a platter. Pour lemon-garlic sauce over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: carrots
directions: Dissolve the bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add carrot and cook until soft.
Drain carrots.
Add butter and parsley to taste. Serve hot.

title: birthday blueberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, butter, 2 cups sugar and sour cream.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in blueberries last.
Fold blueberry-flour mixture into egg mixture until blended.
Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin pan to 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk for 1 minute. Then add other ingredients. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare lime gelatin as directed on package.
Chill until slightly thickened, then fold in pineapple.
Pour into 8-inch pan or Pyrex.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Steam carrots, celery and sprouts.

Place chicken between clear plastic wrap and pound with flat mallet to 1/4-inch thick. Saut mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Cook chicken in 2 tablespoons butter for 2 minutes on each side (use more butter if necessary).
Remove chicken.
Add chicken broth and Marsala.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered until liquid is reduced to 1/2.
Return chicken and mushroom mixture to skillet and heat through.
Arrange steamed vegetables and chicken on a serving platter.
Spoon mushroom mixture and sauce on top of chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in well-greased (or sprayed) casserole dish. Mix flour, sugar and spices.
Cut butter into mixture until cornmeal consistency.
Spread over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Mix flour and salt.
Add alternately with whip cream starting and ending with flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: face paint
directions: White:
Mix white shortening, cornstarch and white flour with rubber spatula to a smooth paste.
Add 3 to 4 drops of glycerin for creamy consistency.
Enough for one child's face.
Add several drops of food coloring to make different colors.
Put on with fingers.

title: perky pie crust
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in other ingredients.
Put in pie pan and brown at 400°.
This is a wonderful crust to use with cream pies.

title: quick trick clam chowder
directions: In a large pan, combine potato mix, plus the water and milk called for on the package, clam liquid and onion.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Add clams, 2 1/2 cups milk and butter.
Heat and serve.

title: yvonne's ratatouille(makes 15 to 20 servings)
directions: Wash peppers; halve.
Remove ribs and seeds.
Cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Scrub zucchini.
Cut on diagonal into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Wash mushrooms, slice lengthwise through stems, 1/4-inch thick.
Wash eggplant.
Do not peel.

Cut lengthwise into quarters, then cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices. In 1/4 cup hot oil in large skillet, saute green pepper, mushrooms, onion and garlic for 5 minutes or until onion is transparent.
With slotted spoon, remove to medium bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to skillet.
Saute zucchini, turning frequently, until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Place in same bowl.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Saute eggplant, turning occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Return vegetables to same skillet.
Layer half of tomato wedges on top.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Stir gently, just to combine.
Layer remaining tomato on top.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley.
Simmer mixture over low heat, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove cover.
Cook 5 minutes longer, by stirring occasionally, with pan juices or until liquid has evaporated.
Turn into large serving dish.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: beef braised in barolo wine
directions: Combine the meat, all the vegetables, herbs and wine in a bowl.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for about 24 hours. Remove the meat and dry well (reserve marinade).
Make little cuts on the surface of the meat and fill them with lard.
Brown the meat thoroughly in hot butter and oil in a flameproof casserole.

title: rice dressing
directions: Boil water.
Add rice cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese and onions.
Stir together and add other ingredients.
Stir and add to greased casserole.
Bake at 350 for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: dressing for potato or macaroni salad
directions: Combine yogurt and mayonnaise in a small mixing bowl, whipping until smooth. Add other ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: strawberry and fig jam
directions: Mash figs fine; measure 3 cups.
Add sugar and Jell-O.
Stir good.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Do not put any water in it.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: browned rice
directions: Brown rice in oil with celery and green pepper.
Add consomme, Worcestershire and catsup.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 350° until rice is tender, or cover and finish cooking on top of the stove, 15 minutes at a low flame until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together in bowl and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan or baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and salt; boil until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Beat in the butter and lemon juice.
After separating the egg, beat yolk with a fork.
Add some of the hot mixture.
Add the yolk to the hot mixture and cook for 5 minutes.
Beat the egg white until soft peaks form, then slowly fold into the hot sauce.
Serve warm over plain cake or cupcakes.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Squeeze oranges and lemons.
Crush bananas.
Mix fruits, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Freeze overnight.
Take out 1 hour before serving.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: veggie bar appetizers
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and pat into 2 cookie sheets, pinching seams together.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Ranch dressing and milk.
Beat cream cheese with dressing mixture.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle with green onions, broccoli buds, carrots and Cheddar cheese.
Cut into desired size bars.

title: lo-cal sugarless chocolate cookies
